{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1781418089334,"sessionID":"ses_13b36ae6fffeLx31BHseD4QV23","part":{"id":"prt_ec4cadb740012OBrGIp0SpixsH","messageID":"msg_ec4cad5800011YyuV7QOcYGBmT","sessionID":"ses_13b36ae6fffeLx31BHseD4QV23","snapshot":"39744e5e81dcaf92a97534cfecaaddbe1208174a","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781418094643,"sessionID":"ses_13b36ae6fffeLx31BHseD4QV23","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_dN8eCmiVIiBuwZVvZ7LPo4wS","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-research/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md","offset":261,"limit":380},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-research/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n261: - If either limit is exceeded and no iteration file has been written yet:\n262:   1. Mark the iteration as `\"status\": \"timeout\"` in the JSONL record\n263:   2. Log event: `{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"iteration_timeout\",\"iteration\":N,\"reason\":\"tool_calls|elapsed_time\"}`\n264:   3. Continue to the next iteration (do not retry the timed-out iteration)\n265: - Budget limits are soft caps - if the agent is actively writing its iteration file when the limit is reached, allow completion\n266: \n267: #### Step 4: Evaluate Results\n268: After agent completes:\n269: 1. Verify `{artifact_dir}/iterations/iteration-{NNN}.md` was created\n270: 2. Verify JSONL was appended with iteration record\n271: 3. Run reducer with `{ latestJSONLDelta, newIterationFile, priorReducedState }`\n272:    - This is a **delta refresh**, not a full replay of every historical JSONL row on each iteration.\n273:    - The reducer consumes only the newest JSONL slice plus the latest iteration artifact against the previously reduced packet state.\n274: 4. Verify reducer refreshed `deep-research-strategy.md`, `findings-registry.json`, and `deep-research-dashboard.md`\n275: 5. Verify the refreshed packet surfaces reflect the new iteration evidence\n276: 6. Extract `newInfoRatio` from JSONL record\n277: 7. Track stuck count: skip if `status == \"thought\"` (no change), reset to 0 if `status == \"insight\"` (breakthrough counts as progress), increment if `newInfoRatio < config.convergenceThreshold`, reset otherwise\n278: \n279: #### Step 4a: Generate Dashboard\n280: \n281: After evaluating iteration results, generate a human-readable dashboard:\n282: \n283: 1. Read JSONL state log, findings registry, and strategy.md\n284: 2. Generate or regenerate `research/deep-research-dashboard.md` with the following sections:\n285:    - **Iteration table**: `| run | focus | newInfoRatio | findings count | status |`\n286:    - **Question status**: `X/Y answered` with itemized list (answered vs remaining)\n287:    - **Trend**: Last 3 newInfoRatio values with direction indicator (ascending, descending, flat)\n288:    - **Dead ends**: Consolidated from all iteration `ruledOut` data\n289:    - **Next focus**: Current value from strategy.md\n290:    - **Active risks**: Guard violations, stuck count, budget warnings\n291: 3. Log event: `{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"dashboard_generated\",\"iteration\":N}`\n292: 4. The dashboard is **auto-generated only** - never manually edited\n293: 5. The dashboard file is overwritten each iteration (not appended)\n294: 6. Dashboard generation is non-blocking: if it fails, log a warning and continue the loop\n295: \n296: In **confirm mode**, the dashboard is displayed to the user at each iteration approval gate. In **auto mode**, it is written silently for post-hoc review.\n297: \n298: #### Step 4b: Checkpoint Commit (REFERENCE-ONLY)\n299: \n300: This checkpointing pattern is documented for reference, but current runtimes should not assume it is available.\n301: \n302: After each iteration is verified (JSONL appended, iteration file written, reducer outputs refreshed):\n303: \n304: 1. **Stage targeted files only** (never `git add -A`):\n305:    ```bash\n306:    git add research/iterations/iteration-{NNN}.md\n307:    git add research/deep-research-state.jsonl\n308:    git add research/deep-research-strategy.md\n309:    git add research/findings-registry.json\n310:    git add research/deep-research-dashboard.md\n311:    git add research/research.md  # if it exists\n312:    ```\n313: 2. **Sanitize**: Exclude `.env`, credentials, large binaries from staging\n314: 3. **Commit**: `git commit -m \"chore(deep-research): iteration {NNN} complete\"`\n315: 4. **On commit failure**: Log warning and continue (checkpoint is non-blocking)\n316: \n317: Checkpoint commits provide rollback points: `git log -- research/` shows the last good state for the research packet. If state corruption occurs, `git checkout HEAD~1 -- research/deep-research-state.jsonl` restores the previous version.\n318: \n319: #### Step 5: Loop Decision\n320: - If convergence check returns STOP: exit to synthesis\n321: - If STUCK_RECOVERY: modify focus directive, reset stuck count, continue\n322: - Otherwise: increment iteration counter, go to Step 1\n323: \n324: ### Ideas Backlog Convention\n325: \n326: A persistent ideas file at `research/research-ideas.md` serves as a parking lot for promising directions not yet pursued.\n327: \n328: #### Check Points\n329: \n330: The orchestrator checks the ideas backlog at three points:\n331: \n332: 1. **Init**: During strategy initialization, if `research/research-ideas.md` exists from a prior session, read it and incorporate relevant ideas into the initial key questions or \"Next Focus\"\n333: 2. **Stuck**: During stuck recovery (Step 2a of the recovery protocol in convergence.md), check ideas backlog before defaulting to generic recovery strategies. Deferred ideas often provide the best escape from stuck states\n334: 3. **Resume**: On auto-resume, read the ideas file alongside JSONL and strategy.md to restore full context\n335: \n336: #### Format\n337: \n338: ```markdown\n339: Title: Research Ideas\n340: \n341: Section: Deferred (not yet explored)\n342: - [Idea description] (noted iteration N: [why deferred])\n343: - [Idea description] (noted iteration N: [why deferred])\n344: \n345: Section: Promoted (moved to Key Questions)\n346: - [Idea] -> promoted to Key Question in iteration N\n347: ```\n348: \n349: Users can edit `research-ideas.md` between sessions to steer future iterations. Agents append new ideas during iterations when they encounter promising tangents that fall outside the current focus.\n350: \n351: ### Stuck Recovery Protocol\n352: When stuckThreshold consecutive iterations show no progress (default: 3, configurable via config.json):\n353: \n354: **Step 0: Classify Failure Mode**\n355: Before selecting a recovery strategy, classify why progress stalled:\n356: 1. Read the last N iteration files (where N = stuckThreshold) to determine the failure pattern\n357: 2. Classify into one of the following modes:\n358:    - `shallow_sources` - iterations find content but lack depth or authoritative sources\n359:    - `contradictory` - iterations return conflicting information without resolution\n360:    - `too_broad` - focus area is too wide, producing scattered low-value findings\n361:    - `repetitive` - iterations keep rediscovering the same information\n362:    - `exhausted` - the topic area has been thoroughly explored with diminishing returns\n363: 3. Select a targeted recovery prompt based on the classification (see convergence.md §4 for category-specific strategies)\n364: 4. Log classification: `{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"stuck_classified\",\"mode\":\"<classification>\",\"iteration\":N}`\n365: \n366: **Steps 1-5: Execute Recovery**\n367: 1. Read strategy.md \"What Worked\" section\n368: 2. Identify least-explored question from \"Key Questions\"\n369: 3. Set next focus to: \"RECOVERY: Widen scope to {least-explored-area}. Try a fundamentally different approach.\" (refined by classification)\n370: 4. Reset stuck counter\n371: 5. If recovery iteration also shows no progress: exit to synthesis with gaps documented\n372: \n373: ### Step 3b: Direct Mode Fallback (REFERENCE-ONLY)\n374: \n375: When agent dispatch fails after the earlier recovery tiers are exhausted:\n376: \n377: 1. Detect dispatch failure: Task tool timeout, API overload (529), or agent crash\n378: 2. Log event: `{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"direct_mode\",\"iteration\":N,\"reason\":\"dispatch_failure\"}`\n379: 3. Orchestrator absorbs the iteration work:\n380:    - Read state files (JSONL + strategy.md)\n381:    - Determine focus from strategy \"Next Focus\"\n382:    - Execute 3-5 research actions directly\n383:    - Write `research/iterations/iteration-NNN.md`\n384:    - Update strategy.md\n385:    - Append iteration record to JSONL\n386: 4. Continue loop normally after direct-mode iteration completes\n387: 5. If direct mode also fails, escalate to the final user-escalation tier\n388: \n389: **Note**: Direct mode iterations are logged with `\"directMode\": true` in their JSONL record for diagnostic tracking.\n390: \n391: ---\n392: \n393: ## 4. WAVE ORCHESTRATION PROTOCOL (REFERENCE-ONLY)\n394: \n395: An optional parallel execution concept for research topics with multiple independent questions. Treat this as reference guidance only; the live workflow remains sequential and does **not** emit wave-specific JSONL events or routing today.\n396: \n397: ### When to Use Waves\n398: \n399: - 3+ independent key questions identified during initialization\n400: - Questions do not depend on each other's answers\n401: - Parallelism is beneficial (time-constrained research, broad survey)\n402: \n403: ### Wave Execution Model (conceptual only)\n404: \n405: ```text\n406: Wave 1: Dispatch N agents on independent questions\n407:   |\n408:   +-- Agent A: Question 1 --> iteration-001.md (newInfoRatio: 0.8)\n409:   +-- Agent B: Question 2 --> iteration-002.md (newInfoRatio: 0.3)\n410:   +-- Agent C: Question 3 --> iteration-003.md (newInfoRatio: 0.7)\n411:   |\n412: Scoring: Rank by newInfoRatio, prune below median only in a future runtime that explicitly adds wave support\n413:   |\n414: Wave 2: Follow-up on top-K questions (K = ceil(N/2))\n415:   +-- Agent A: Question 1 follow-up --> iteration-004.md\n416:   +-- Agent C: Question 3 follow-up --> iteration-005.md\n417:   |\n418: Repeat until convergence\n419: ```\n420: \n421: ### Scoring and Pruning\n422: \n423: In a future wave-enabled runtime:\n424: 1. Rank all wave iterations by `newInfoRatio`\n425: 2. Compute wave median: `median([i.newInfoRatio for i in wave_iterations])`\n426: 3. **Prune**: Questions with newInfoRatio below median would be deprioritized\n427: 4. **Promote**: Top-K questions (K = ceil(N/2)) would get follow-up iterations\n428: 5. Pruned questions would move to the ideas backlog, not be discarded\n429: \n430: ### Breakthrough Detection\n431: \n432: When any single iteration in a wave achieves `newInfoRatio > 2x wave_average`:\n433: \n434: 1. Flag as **breakthrough**: `{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"breakthrough\",\"iteration\":N,\"ratio\":X.XX}`\n435: 2. Generate 2-3 adjacent questions from the breakthrough findings\n436: 3. Prioritize these adjacent questions in the next wave\n437: 4. Breakthrough iterations are NEVER pruned\n438: \n439: ### Wave JSONL Records\n440: \n441: Wave-specific fields and events are **not part of the current persisted contract**. Until a runtime explicitly ships wave support, keep iteration records and events on the standard sequential schema only.\n442: \n443: ### Integration with Sequential Loop\n444: \n445: - Waves are an ALTERNATIVE to sequential iteration, not a replacement\n446: - The convergence algorithm applies identically (uses all iteration records)\n447: - A future wave-capable runtime could transition back to sequential mode when questions narrow to 1-2\n448: - The current runtime never spawns a wave automatically\n449: \n450: ---\n451: \n452: ## 5. CONTEXT ISOLATION DISPATCH (EXPERIMENTAL, REFERENCE-ONLY)\n453: \n454: An alternative dispatch mechanism that guarantees fresh context per iteration by launching a new OS process. Treat this as reference-only unless the runtime explicitly implements alternate CLI dispatch.\n455: \n456: ### Motivation\n457: \n458: The standard dispatch (Task tool) shares the parent session's token budget. In long research sessions (10+ iterations), this may cause context compression that degrades reasoning quality. Process-level isolation eliminates this risk.\n459: \n460: ### Dispatch Mechanism\n461: \n462: Replace Task tool dispatch with shell-level `claude -p` invocation:\n463: \n464: 1. **Generate prompt**: Orchestrator builds a self-contained prompt from:\n465:    - Strategy.md (current state)\n466:    - Config.json (parameters)\n467:    - Last N iteration summaries (from JSONL)\n468:    - Compact state summary (Step 2b)\n469:    - Full agent protocol instructions\n470: 2. **Write to temp file**: `scratch/.dispatch-prompt-{NNN}.md`\n471: 3. **Execute**: `claude -p \"$(cat scratch/.dispatch-prompt-{NNN}.md)\" --max-turns 50 --output-format json`\n472: 4. **Collect output**: Agent writes iteration file directly to disk\n473: 5. **Verify**: Orchestrator checks iteration file and JSONL were created\n474: 6. **Cleanup**: Remove temp prompt file\n475: \n476: ### Trade-offs\n477: \n478: | Aspect | Task Tool Dispatch | `claude -p` Dispatch |\n479: |--------|-------------------|---------------------|\n480: | Context freshness | Shared budget, may degrade | Guaranteed fresh |\n481: | Token cost | Lower (cached context) | Higher (full context per call) |\n482: | Latency | Lower (in-process) | Higher (new process startup) |\n483: | Context size | Limited by parent budget | Full model context available |\n484: | Error handling | In-process exceptions | Process exit codes |\n485: \n486: ### When to Use\n487: \n488: - Autonomous/unattended research sessions (overnight runs)\n489: - Research past iteration 8+ where context degradation is measurable\n490: - Critical research where reasoning quality must not degrade\n491: \n492: **Status**: Reference-only. Track adoption based on need for fully autonomous overnight research sessions.\n493: \n494: ---\n495: \n496: ## 6. PHASE: SYNTHESIS\n497: \n498: ### Purpose\n499: Compile all iteration findings into final research/research.md. The synthesis workflow owns the canonical `research/research.md` output.\n500: \n501: ### Steps\n502: \n503: 1. **Read all iteration files**: `research/iterations/iteration-*.md`\n504: 2. **Read strategy.md**: Final state of questions, approaches\n505: 3. **Compile research/research.md**: Merge findings into 17-section format\n506:    - Deduplicate overlapping findings\n507:    - Organize by section topic\n508:    - Add citations from iteration files\n509:    - Cite `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` in the References section when `config.resource_map_present == true`\n510:    - Do not synthesize a placeholder reference when `resource-map.md` was absent at init\n511:    - Note unanswered questions in Section 12 (Open Questions)\n512:    - **Include a mandatory \"## Eliminated Alternatives\" section** as primary research output:\n513:      - Consolidate all `ruledOut` entries from iteration JSONL records\n514:      - Consolidate all `## Dead Ends` sections from iteration files\n515:      - Format as a table: `| Approach | Reason Eliminated | Evidence | Iteration(s) |`\n516:      - This section documents negative knowledge (what was tried and why it failed)\n517:      - Treat as primary research output - not an appendix or afterthought\n518:      - Place after Section 11 (Recommendations) and before Section 12 (Open Questions)\n519: 4. **If reopening a completed packet later**: snapshot this file as `research/synthesis-v{generation}.md` before any `completed-continue` flow\n520: 5. **Update config status**: Set `status: \"complete\"` in config.json\n521: 6. **Final JSONL entry**: `{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"synthesis_complete\",\"totalIterations\":N,\"answeredCount\":A,\"totalQuestions\":Q,\"stopReason\":\"converged\"}`\n522: \n523: ### Progressive vs Final Synthesis\n524: - If `progressiveSynthesis: true` (default): research/research.md was updated each iteration. Final synthesis is a cleanup pass.\n525: - If `progressiveSynthesis: false`: research/research.md is created from scratch during synthesis.\n526: \n527: ---\n528: \n529: ## 7. PHASE: SAVE\n530: \n531: ### Purpose\n532: Preserve research context to memory system.\n533: \n534: ### Steps\n535: \n536: 1. **Generate context**: `node .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/dist/memory/generate-context.js {spec_folder}`\n537: 2. **No extra indexing step in the live contract**: `generate-context.js` is the supported save boundary for this workflow\n538: 3. **Verify**: Confirm memory/*.md file created with proper anchors\n539: \n540: ---\n541: \n542: ## 8. STATE TRANSITIONS\n543: \n544: ```text\n545: [INITIALIZED] --> config + strategy + state created\n546:     |\n547: [ITERATING] --> agent dispatched, executing research\n548:     |\n549: [EVALUATING] --> iteration complete, checking convergence\n550:     |\n551:     |-- newInfoRatio >= threshold --> [ITERATING]\n552:     |-- stuck_count >= stuckThreshold --> [STUCK_RECOVERY]\n553:     |-- converged or max_iterations --> [SYNTHESIZING]\n554: \n555: [STUCK_RECOVERY] --> widen focus, try different approach\n556:     |\n557:     |-- recovered (newInfoRatio > 0) --> [ITERATING]\n558:     |-- still stuck --> [SYNTHESIZING] (gaps documented)\n559: \n560: [SYNTHESIZING] --> final research/research.md compilation\n561:     |\n562: [SAVING] --> memory context preservation\n563:     |\n564: [COMPLETE] --> all artifacts created, loop finished\n565: ```\n566: \n567: Hook-capable and non-hook runtimes must follow the same state machine. Hooks may pre-prime context, but they must not change which lifecycle branch the packet selects.\n568: \n569: ---\n570: \n571: ## 9. ERROR HANDLING\n572: \n573: | Error | Phase | Action |\n574: |-------|-------|--------|\n575: | Agent dispatch timeout | Loop | Retry once with reduced scope. If second timeout, mark iteration as \"timeout\" and continue |\n576: | WebFetch fails | Loop | Log URL in iteration file, try alternative source, continue with available data |\n577: | State file missing | Init/Loop | If JSONL missing: re-initialize. If strategy missing: reconstruct from JSONL |\n578: | JSONL malformed | Loop | Skip malformed lines, reconstruct from valid entries |\n579: | 3+ consecutive failures | Loop | Halt loop, enter synthesis with partial findings |\n580: | Agent dispatch failure (API overload, timeout) | Loop | Escalate through the documented recovery ladder in order. Direct mode fallback is reference-only unless the runtime explicitly supports it. |\n581: | Memory save fails | Save | Preserve the current `{artifact_dir}` packet as backup, then log the error |\n582: \n583: ### State Recovery Protocol\n584: \n585: When state files are missing or corrupted, apply this 5-priority cascade:\n586: \n587: | Priority | Condition | Recovery Action |\n588: |----------|-----------|----------------|\n589: | 1 (Primary) | JSONL exists and parseable | Normal operation (with fault-tolerant parsing) |\n590: | 2 (Strategy rebuild) | JSONL exists, strategy.md missing | Reconstruct strategy from JSONL: extract questions, focus areas, newInfoRatio trend. Create minimal strategy.md |\n591: | 3 (JSONL reconstruction) | JSONL missing/corrupt, iteration files exist | Scan `research/iterations/iteration-*.md`, parse Assessment sections, reconstruct JSONL with `status: \"reconstructed\"` |\n592: | 4 (Config-only restart) | Only config.json remains | Restart from initialization phase using config parameters. Log: `{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"fresh_restart\",\"reason\":\"state_files_missing\"}` |\n593: | 5 (Abort) | Config.json also missing | Cannot recover. Report error and halt. |\n594: \n595: Each priority level is attempted in order. If a level fails, fall through to the next. See state_format.md for JSONL reconstruction details.\n596: \n597: ---\n598: \n599: ## 10. CONFIRM MODE ADDITIONS\n600: \n601: In confirm mode, the YAML workflow adds approval gates:\n602: \n603: | Gate Location | Behavior |\n604: |---------------|----------|\n605: | After initialization | Show config and initial strategy. Wait for approval |\n606: | After each iteration | Show iteration findings and convergence status. Options: Continue, Adjust Focus, Stop |\n607: | Before synthesis | Show summary of all iterations. Wait for approval to synthesize |\n608: | After synthesis | Show final research/research.md summary. Approve or request revisions |\n609: \n610: ---\n611: \n612: ## 11. REVIEW MODE ROUTING\n613: \n614: Deep-review lifecycle, convergence, state schemas, traceability protocols, and report contracts live in the sibling `deep-review` skill.\n615: \n616: This reference keeps only the routing rule: do not document or execute review-mode loop behavior from `deep-research`. Route review requests to `deep-review/SKILL.md` and its references.\n\n(End of file - total 616 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"- If either limit is exceeded and no iteration file has been written yet:\n  1. Mark the iteration as `\"status\": \"timeout\"` in the JSONL record\n  2. Log event: `{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"iteration_timeout\",\"iteration\":N,\"reason\":\"tool_calls|elapsed_time\"}`\n  3. Continue to the next iteration (do not retry the timed-out iteration)\n- Budget limits are soft caps - if the agent is actively writing its iteration file when the limit is reached, allow completion\n\n#### Step 4: Evaluate Results\nAfter agent completes:\n1. Verify `{artifact_dir}/iterations/iteration-{NNN}.md` was created\n2. Verify JSONL was appended with iteration record\n3. Run reducer with `{ latestJSONLDelta, newIterationFile, priorReducedState }`\n   - This is a **delta refresh**, not a full replay of every historical JSONL row on each iteration.\n   - The reducer consumes only the newest JSONL slice plus the latest iteration artifact against the previously reduced packet state.\n4. Verify reducer refreshed `deep-research-strategy.md`, `findings-registry.json`, and `deep-research-dashboard.md`\n5. Verify the refreshed packet surfaces reflect the new iteration evidence\n6. Extract `newInfoRatio` from JSONL record\n7. Track stuck count: skip if `status == \"thought\"` (no change), reset to 0 if `status == \"insight\"` (breakthrough counts as progress), increment if `newInfoRatio < config.convergenceThreshold`, reset otherwise\n\n#### Step 4a: Generate Dashboard\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-research/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md","text":"- If either limit is exceeded and no iteration file has been written yet:\n  1. Mark the iteration as `\"status\": \"timeout\"` in the JSONL record\n  2. Log event: `{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"iteration_timeout\",\"iteration\":N,\"reason\":\"tool_calls|elapsed_time\"}`\n  3. Continue to the next iteration (do not retry the timed-out iteration)\n- Budget limits are soft caps - if the agent is actively writing its iteration file when the limit is reached, allow completion\n\n#### Step 4: Evaluate Results\nAfter agent completes:\n1. Verify `{artifact_dir}/iterations/iteration-{NNN}.md` was created\n2. Verify JSONL was appended with iteration record\n3. Run reducer with `{ latestJSONLDelta, newIterationFile, priorReducedState }`\n   - This is a **delta refresh**, not a full replay of every historical JSONL row on each iteration.\n   - The reducer consumes only the newest JSONL slice plus the latest iteration artifact against the previously reduced packet state.\n4. Verify reducer refreshed `deep-research-strategy.md`, `findings-registry.json`, and `deep-research-dashboard.md`\n5. Verify the refreshed packet surfaces reflect the new iteration evidence\n6. Extract `newInfoRatio` from JSONL record\n7. Track stuck count: skip if `status == \"thought\"` (no change), reset to 0 if `status == \"insight\"` (breakthrough counts as progress), increment if `newInfoRatio < config.convergenceThreshold`, reset otherwise\n\n#### Step 4a: Generate Dashboard\n\nAfter evaluating iteration results, generate a human-readable dashboard:\n\n1. Read JSONL state log, findings registry, and strategy.md\n2. Generate or regenerate `research/deep-research-dashboard.md` with the following sections:\n   - **Iteration table**: `| run | focus | newInfoRatio | findings count | status |`\n   - **Question status**: `X/Y answered` with itemized list (answered vs remaining)\n   - **Trend**: Last 3 newInfoRatio values with direction indicator (ascending, descending, flat)\n   - **Dead ends**: Consolidated from all iteration `ruledOut` data\n   - **Next focus**: Current value from strategy.md\n   - **Active risks**: Guard violations, stuck count, budget warnings\n3. Log event: `{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"dashboard_generated\",\"iteration\":N}`\n4. The dashboard is **auto-generated only** - never manually edited\n5. The dashboard file is overwritten each iteration (not appended)\n6. Dashboard generation is non-blocking: if it fails, log a warning and continue the loop\n\nIn **confirm mode**, the dashboard is displayed to the user at each iteration approval gate. In **auto mode**, it is written silently for post-hoc review.\n\n#### Step 4b: Checkpoint Commit (REFERENCE-ONLY)\n\nThis checkpointing pattern is documented for reference, but current runtimes should not assume it is available.\n\nAfter each iteration is verified (JSONL appended, iteration file written, reducer outputs refreshed):\n\n1. **Stage targeted files only** (never `git add -A`):\n   ```bash\n   git add research/iterations/iteration-{NNN}.md\n   git add research/deep-research-state.jsonl\n   git add research/deep-research-strategy.md\n   git add research/findings-registry.json\n   git add research/deep-research-dashboard.md\n   git add research/research.md  # if it exists\n   ```\n2. **Sanitize**: Exclude `.env`, credentials, large binaries from staging\n3. **Commit**: `git commit -m \"chore(deep-research): iteration {NNN} complete\"`\n4. **On commit failure**: Log warning and continue (checkpoint is non-blocking)\n\nCheckpoint commits provide rollback points: `git log -- research/` shows the last good state for the research packet. If state corruption occurs, `git checkout HEAD~1 -- research/deep-research-state.jsonl` restores the previous version.\n\n#### Step 5: Loop Decision\n- If convergence check returns STOP: exit to synthesis\n- If STUCK_RECOVERY: modify focus directive, reset stuck count, continue\n- Otherwise: increment iteration counter, go to Step 1\n\n### Ideas Backlog Convention\n\nA persistent ideas file at `research/research-ideas.md` serves as a parking lot for promising directions not yet pursued.\n\n#### Check Points\n\nThe orchestrator checks the ideas backlog at three points:\n\n1. **Init**: During strategy initialization, if `research/research-ideas.md` exists from a prior session, read it and incorporate relevant ideas into the initial key questions or \"Next Focus\"\n2. **Stuck**: During stuck recovery (Step 2a of the recovery protocol in convergence.md), check ideas backlog before defaulting to generic recovery strategies. Deferred ideas often provide the best escape from stuck states\n3. **Resume**: On auto-resume, read the ideas file alongside JSONL and strategy.md to restore full context\n\n#### Format\n\n```markdown\nTitle: Research Ideas\n\nSection: Deferred (not yet explored)\n- [Idea description] (noted iteration N: [why deferred])\n- [Idea description] (noted iteration N: [why deferred])\n\nSection: Promoted (moved to Key Questions)\n- [Idea] -> promoted to Key Question in iteration N\n```\n\nUsers can edit `research-ideas.md` between sessions to steer future iterations. Agents append new ideas during iterations when they encounter promising tangents that fall outside the current focus.\n\n### Stuck Recovery Protocol\nWhen stuckThreshold consecutive iterations show no progress (default: 3, configurable via config.json):\n\n**Step 0: Classify Failure Mode**\nBefore selecting a recovery strategy, classify why progress stalled:\n1. Read the last N iteration files (where N = stuckThreshold) to determine the failure pattern\n2. Classify into one of the following modes:\n   - `shallow_sources` - iterations find content but lack depth or authoritative sources\n   - `contradictory` - iterations return conflicting information without resolution\n   - `too_broad` - focus area is too wide, producing scattered low-value findings\n   - `repetitive` - iterations keep rediscovering the same information\n   - `exhausted` - the topic area has been thoroughly explored with diminishing returns\n3. Select a targeted recovery prompt based on the classification (see convergence.md §4 for category-specific strategies)\n4. Log classification: `{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"stuck_classified\",\"mode\":\"<classification>\",\"iteration\":N}`\n\n**Steps 1-5: Execute Recovery**\n1. Read strategy.md \"What Worked\" section\n2. Identify least-explored question from \"Key Questions\"\n3. Set next focus to: \"RECOVERY: Widen scope to {least-explored-area}. Try a fundamentally different approach.\" (refined by classification)\n4. Reset stuck counter\n5. If recovery iteration also shows no progress: exit to synthesis with gaps documented\n\n### Step 3b: Direct Mode Fallback (REFERENCE-ONLY)\n\nWhen agent dispatch fails after the earlier recovery tiers are exhausted:\n\n1. Detect dispatch failure: Task tool timeout, API overload (529), or agent crash\n2. Log event: `{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"direct_mode\",\"iteration\":N,\"reason\":\"dispatch_failure\"}`\n3. Orchestrator absorbs the iteration work:\n   - Read state files (JSONL + strategy.md)\n   - Determine focus from strategy \"Next Focus\"\n   - Execute 3-5 research actions directly\n   - Write `research/iterations/iteration-NNN.md`\n   - Update strategy.md\n   - Append iteration record to JSONL\n4. Continue loop normally after direct-mode iteration completes\n5. If direct mode also fails, escalate to the final user-escalation tier\n\n**Note**: Direct mode iterations are logged with `\"directMode\": true` in their JSONL record for diagnostic tracking.\n\n---\n\n## 4. WAVE ORCHESTRATION PROTOCOL (REFERENCE-ONLY)\n\nAn optional parallel execution concept for research topics with multiple independent questions. Treat this as reference guidance only; the live workflow remains sequential and does **not** emit wave-specific JSONL events or routing today.\n\n### When to Use Waves\n\n- 3+ independent key questions identified during initialization\n- Questions do not depend on each other's answers\n- Parallelism is beneficial (time-constrained research, broad survey)\n\n### Wave Execution Model (conceptual only)\n\n```text\nWave 1: Dispatch N agents on independent questions\n  |\n  +-- Agent A: Question 1 --> iteration-001.md (newInfoRatio: 0.8)\n  +-- Agent B: Question 2 --> iteration-002.md (newInfoRatio: 0.3)\n  +-- Agent C: Question 3 --> iteration-003.md (newInfoRatio: 0.7)\n  |\nScoring: Rank by newInfoRatio, prune below median only in a future runtime that explicitly adds wave support\n  |\nWave 2: Follow-up on top-K questions (K = ceil(N/2))\n  +-- Agent A: Question 1 follow-up --> iteration-004.md\n  +-- Agent C: Question 3 follow-up --> iteration-005.md\n  |\nRepeat until convergence\n```\n\n### Scoring and Pruning\n\nIn a future wave-enabled runtime:\n1. Rank all wave iterations by `newInfoRatio`\n2. Compute wave median: `median([i.newInfoRatio for i in wave_iterations])`\n3. **Prune**: Questions with newInfoRatio below median would be deprioritized\n4. **Promote**: Top-K questions (K = ceil(N/2)) would get follow-up iterations\n5. Pruned questions would move to the ideas backlog, not be discarded\n\n### Breakthrough Detection\n\nWhen any single iteration in a wave achieves `newInfoRatio > 2x wave_average`:\n\n1. Flag as **breakthrough**: `{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"breakthrough\",\"iteration\":N,\"ratio\":X.XX}`\n2. Generate 2-3 adjacent questions from the breakthrough findings\n3. Prioritize these adjacent questions in the next wave\n4. Breakthrough iterations are NEVER pruned\n\n### Wave JSONL Records\n\nWave-specific fields and events are **not part of the current persisted contract**. Until a runtime explicitly ships wave support, keep iteration records and events on the standard sequential schema only.\n\n### Integration with Sequential Loop\n\n- Waves are an ALTERNATIVE to sequential iteration, not a replacement\n- The convergence algorithm applies identically (uses all iteration records)\n- A future wave-capable runtime could transition back to sequential mode when questions narrow to 1-2\n- The current runtime never spawns a wave automatically\n\n---\n\n## 5. CONTEXT ISOLATION DISPATCH (EXPERIMENTAL, REFERENCE-ONLY)\n\nAn alternative dispatch mechanism that guarantees fresh context per iteration by launching a new OS process. Treat this as reference-only unless the runtime explicitly implements alternate CLI dispatch.\n\n### Motivation\n\nThe standard dispatch (Task tool) shares the parent session's token budget. In long research sessions (10+ iterations), this may cause context compression that degrades reasoning quality. Process-level isolation eliminates this risk.\n\n### Dispatch Mechanism\n\nReplace Task tool dispatch with shell-level `claude -p` invocation:\n\n1. **Generate prompt**: Orchestrator builds a self-contained prompt from:\n   - Strategy.md (current state)\n   - Config.json (parameters)\n   - Last N iteration summaries (from JSONL)\n   - Compact state summary (Step 2b)\n   - Full agent protocol instructions\n2. **Write to temp file**: `scratch/.dispatch-prompt-{NNN}.md`\n3. **Execute**: `claude -p \"$(cat scratch/.dispatch-prompt-{NNN}.md)\" --max-turns 50 --output-format json`\n4. **Collect output**: Agent writes iteration file directly to disk\n5. **Verify**: Orchestrator checks iteration file and JSONL were created\n6. **Cleanup**: Remove temp prompt file\n\n### Trade-offs\n\n| Aspect | Task Tool Dispatch | `claude -p` Dispatch |\n|--------|-------------------|---------------------|\n| Context freshness | Shared budget, may degrade | Guaranteed fresh |\n| Token cost | Lower (cached context) | Higher (full context per call) |\n| Latency | Lower (in-process) | Higher (new process startup) |\n| Context size | Limited by parent budget | Full model context available |\n| Error handling | In-process exceptions | Process exit codes |\n\n### When to Use\n\n- Autonomous/unattended research sessions (overnight runs)\n- Research past iteration 8+ where context degradation is measurable\n- Critical research where reasoning quality must not degrade\n\n**Status**: Reference-only. Track adoption based on need for fully autonomous overnight research sessions.\n\n---\n\n## 6. PHASE: SYNTHESIS\n\n### Purpose\nCompile all iteration findings into final research/research.md. The synthesis workflow owns the canonical `research/research.md` output.\n\n### Steps\n\n1. **Read all iteration files**: `research/iterations/iteration-*.md`\n2. **Read strategy.md**: Final state of questions, approaches\n3. **Compile research/research.md**: Merge findings into 17-section format\n   - Deduplicate overlapping findings\n   - Organize by section topic\n   - Add citations from iteration files\n   - Cite `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` in the References section when `config.resource_map_present == true`\n   - Do not synthesize a placeholder reference when `resource-map.md` was absent at init\n   - Note unanswered questions in Section 12 (Open Questions)\n   - **Include a mandatory \"## Eliminated Alternatives\" section** as primary research output:\n     - Consolidate all `ruledOut` entries from iteration JSONL records\n     - Consolidate all `## Dead Ends` sections from iteration files\n     - Format as a table: `| Approach | Reason Eliminated | Evidence | Iteration(s) |`\n     - This section documents negative knowledge (what was tried and why it failed)\n     - Treat as primary research output - not an appendix or afterthought\n     - Place after Section 11 (Recommendations) and before Section 12 (Open Questions)\n4. **If reopening a completed packet later**: snapshot this file as `research/synthesis-v{generation}.md` before any `completed-continue` flow\n5. **Update config status**: Set `status: \"complete\"` in config.json\n6. **Final JSONL entry**: `{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"synthesis_complete\",\"totalIterations\":N,\"answeredCount\":A,\"totalQuestions\":Q,\"stopReason\":\"converged\"}`\n\n### Progressive vs Final Synthesis\n- If `progressiveSynthesis: true` (default): research/research.md was updated each iteration. Final synthesis is a cleanup pass.\n- If `progressiveSynthesis: false`: research/research.md is created from scratch during synthesis.\n\n---\n\n## 7. PHASE: SAVE\n\n### Purpose\nPreserve research context to memory system.\n\n### Steps\n\n1. **Generate context**: `node .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/dist/memory/generate-context.js {spec_folder}`\n2. **No extra indexing step in the live contract**: `generate-context.js` is the supported save boundary for this workflow\n3. **Verify**: Confirm memory/*.md file created with proper anchors\n\n---\n\n## 8. STATE TRANSITIONS\n\n```text\n[INITIALIZED] --> config + strategy + state created\n    |\n[ITERATING] --> agent dispatched, executing research\n    |\n[EVALUATING] --> iteration complete, checking convergence\n    |\n    |-- newInfoRatio >= threshold --> [ITERATING]\n    |-- stuck_count >= stuckThreshold --> [STUCK_RECOVERY]\n    |-- converged or max_iterations --> [SYNTHESIZING]\n\n[STUCK_RECOVERY] --> widen focus, try different approach\n    |\n    |-- recovered (newInfoRatio > 0) --> [ITERATING]\n    |-- still stuck --> [SYNTHESIZING] (gaps documented)\n\n[SYNTHESIZING] --> final research/research.md compilation\n    |\n[SAVING] --> memory context preservation\n    |\n[COMPLETE] --> all artifacts created, loop finished\n```\n\nHook-capable and non-hook runtimes must follow the same state machine. Hooks may pre-prime context, but they must not change which lifecycle branch the packet selects.\n\n---\n\n## 9. ERROR HANDLING\n\n| Error | Phase | Action |\n|-------|-------|--------|\n| Agent dispatch timeout | Loop | Retry once with reduced scope. If second timeout, mark iteration as \"timeout\" and continue |\n| WebFetch fails | Loop | Log URL in iteration file, try alternative source, continue with available data |\n| State file missing | Init/Loop | If JSONL missing: re-initialize. If strategy missing: reconstruct from JSONL |\n| JSONL malformed | Loop | Skip malformed lines, reconstruct from valid entries |\n| 3+ consecutive failures | Loop | Halt loop, enter synthesis with partial findings |\n| Agent dispatch failure (API overload, timeout) | Loop | Escalate through the documented recovery ladder in order. Direct mode fallback is reference-only unless the runtime explicitly supports it. |\n| Memory save fails | Save | Preserve the current `{artifact_dir}` packet as backup, then log the error |\n\n### State Recovery Protocol\n\nWhen state files are missing or corrupted, apply this 5-priority cascade:\n\n| Priority | Condition | Recovery Action |\n|----------|-----------|----------------|\n| 1 (Primary) | JSONL exists and parseable | Normal operation (with fault-tolerant parsing) |\n| 2 (Strategy rebuild) | JSONL exists, strategy.md missing | Reconstruct strategy from JSONL: extract questions, focus areas, newInfoRatio trend. Create minimal strategy.md |\n| 3 (JSONL reconstruction) | JSONL missing/corrupt, iteration files exist | Scan `research/iterations/iteration-*.md`, parse Assessment sections, reconstruct JSONL with `status: \"reconstructed\"` |\n| 4 (Config-only restart) | Only config.json remains | Restart from initialization phase using config parameters. Log: `{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"fresh_restart\",\"reason\":\"state_files_missing\"}` |\n| 5 (Abort) | Config.json also missing | Cannot recover. Report error and halt. |\n\nEach priority level is attempted in order. If a level fails, fall through to the next. See state_format.md for JSONL reconstruction details.\n\n---\n\n## 10. CONFIRM MODE ADDITIONS\n\nIn confirm mode, the YAML workflow adds approval gates:\n\n| Gate Location | Behavior |\n|---------------|----------|\n| After initialization | Show config and initial strategy. Wait for approval |\n| After each iteration | Show iteration findings and convergence status. Options: Continue, Adjust Focus, Stop |\n| Before synthesis | Show summary of all iterations. Wait for approval to synthesize |\n| After synthesis | Show final research/research.md summary. Approve or request revisions |\n\n---\n\n## 11. REVIEW MODE ROUTING\n\nDeep-review lifecycle, convergence, state schemas, traceability protocols, and report contracts live in the sibling `deep-review` skill.\n\nThis reference keeps only the routing rule: do not document or execute review-mode loop behavior from `deep-research`. Route review requests to `deep-review/SKILL.md` and its references.","lineStart":261,"lineEnd":616,"totalLines":616,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-research/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md","time":{"start":1781418094637,"end":1781418094641}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_07f72eb8a7cbf848016a2e486e93f881919a0aa5a7c926d9f6"}},"id":"prt_ec4caf024001ysd2otqBoVg8pl","sessionID":"ses_13b36ae6fffeLx31BHseD4QV23","messageID":"msg_ec4cad5800011YyuV7QOcYGBmT"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781418094677,"sessionID":"ses_13b36ae6fffeLx31BHseD4QV23","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_dFRAFmS36lS7UC1QElFjOOZL","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-research/references/state/state_jsonl.md","offset":1,"limit":320},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-research/references/state/state_jsonl.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: Deep Research JSONL State Reference\n3: description: Config, iteration, event, lineage, graph, and blocked-stop records for deep-research state logs.\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"research state jsonl\"\n6:   - \"research config record\"\n7:   - \"research iteration records\"\n8:   - \"research negative knowledge\"\n9:   - \"research graph events\"\n10:   - \"research event records\"\n11: importance_tier: normal\n12: contextType: implementation\n13: ---\n14: \n15: # Deep Research JSONL State Reference\n16: \n17: `deep-research-state.jsonl` is append-only. Each line is one JSON object. The first line is normally the config record, followed by iteration and event records.\n18: \n19: ---\n20: \n21: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n22: \n23: ### Purpose\n24: \n25: Define the append-only JSONL records used by deep-research config, iteration, lifecycle, graph, pause, stuck-recovery, and blocked-stop state.\n26: \n27: ### When to Use\n28: \n29: Load this reference when validating state logs, adding event records, reconstructing a packet, or mapping legacy stop labels to current values.\n30: \n31: ### Core Principle\n32: \n33: Raw JSONL is append-only evidence. Reducer-owned files derive from it, but they do not replace it.\n34: \n35: ---\n36: \n37: ## 2. CONFIG RECORD\n38: \n39: The config record captures the initialized loop contract.\n40: \n41: ```json\n42: {\n43:   \"type\": \"config\",\n44:   \"topic\": \"API response time optimization\",\n45:   \"maxIterations\": 10,\n46:   \"convergenceThreshold\": 0.05,\n47:   \"stuckThreshold\": 3,\n48:   \"specFolder\": \"028-auto-deep-research\",\n49:   \"createdAt\": \"2026-05-24T00:00:00Z\"\n50: }\n51: ```\n52: \n53: The full config file also stores executor, lineage, reducer, capability matrix, pause sentinel, archive, and file-protection settings.\n54: \n55: ---\n56: \n57: ## 3. ITERATION RECORDS\n58: \n59: ```json\n60: {\n61:   \"type\": \"iteration\",\n62:   \"run\": 1,\n63:   \"status\": \"complete\",\n64:   \"focus\": \"Initial broad survey\",\n65:   \"findingsCount\": 5,\n66:   \"newInfoRatio\": 1.0,\n67:   \"noveltyJustification\": \"First pass; all findings are new to this packet\",\n68:   \"keyQuestions\": [\"What causes latency?\"],\n69:   \"answeredQuestions\": [\"What causes latency?\"],\n70:   \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-24T00:05:00Z\",\n71:   \"durationMs\": 45000\n72: }\n73: ```\n74: \n75: | Field | Required | Notes |\n76: |-------|----------|-------|\n77: | `type` | Yes | `iteration` |\n78: | `run` | Yes | 1-indexed iteration number |\n79: | `status` | Yes | See status values below |\n80: | `focus` | Yes | Single focus investigated |\n81: | `findingsCount` | Yes | Number of findings reported |\n82: | `newInfoRatio` | Yes | Novelty score used by convergence |\n83: | `noveltyJustification` | Recommended | One-sentence explanation of the ratio |\n84: | `keyQuestions` | Recommended | Questions considered during this iteration |\n85: | `answeredQuestions` | Recommended | Questions answered by evidence |\n86: | `ruledOut` | Optional | Negative knowledge entries |\n87: | `graphEvents` | Optional | Coverage graph mutations |\n88: \n89: Status values:\n90: \n91: | Status | Meaning |\n92: |--------|---------|\n93: | `complete` | Normal evidence-gathering iteration |\n94: | `timeout` | Time/tool budget exceeded |\n95: | `error` | Tool, parse, or unexpected failure |\n96: | `stuck` | No new information and no clear next direction |\n97: | `insight` | Low ratio but important conceptual breakthrough |\n98: | `thought` | Analytical-only iteration; excluded from stuck and signal math |\n99: \n100: ---\n101: \n102: ## 4. CONVERGENCE SIGNAL FIELDS\n103: \n104: When the composite algorithm runs, the iteration may include signal values:\n105: \n106: ```json\n107: {\n108:   \"type\": \"iteration\",\n109:   \"run\": 5,\n110:   \"convergenceSignals\": {\n111:     \"rollingAvg\": 0.12,\n112:     \"madScore\": 0.08,\n113:     \"entropyCoverage\": 0.71,\n114:     \"compositeStop\": 0.42\n115:   }\n116: }\n117: ```\n118: \n119: Signal rules live in `../convergence/convergence_signals.md`.\n120: \n121: ---\n122: \n123: ## 5. NEGATIVE KNOWLEDGE\n124: \n125: Use `ruledOut` to preserve eliminated approaches.\n126: \n127: ```json\n128: {\n129:   \"type\": \"iteration\",\n130:   \"run\": 3,\n131:   \"status\": \"complete\",\n132:   \"ruledOut\": [\n133:     {\n134:       \"approach\": \"HTTP/3 multiplexing\",\n135:       \"reason\": \"No server-side support in target environment\",\n136:       \"evidence\": \"file:docs/protocols.md:42\"\n137:     }\n138:   ]\n139: }\n140: ```\n141: \n142: Ruled-out directions should also appear in strategy and synthesis outputs.\n143: \n144: ---\n145: \n146: ## 6. GRAPH EVENTS\n147: \n148: `graphEvents` records coverage graph mutations from an iteration.\n149: \n150: ```json\n151: {\n152:   \"type\": \"iteration\",\n153:   \"run\": 4,\n154:   \"graphEvents\": [\n155:     {\"type\": \"question\", \"id\": \"q-reconnect\", \"label\": \"How should reconnect work?\"},\n156:     {\"type\": \"finding\", \"id\": \"f-backoff\", \"label\": \"Exponential backoff is required\"},\n157:     {\"type\": \"edge\", \"from\": \"f-backoff\", \"to\": \"q-reconnect\", \"relation\": \"ANSWERS\"}\n158:   ]\n159: }\n160: ```\n161: \n162: Valid node types are `question`, `finding`, `claim`, and `source`; `edge` records connect nodes. IDs must be unique within a single `(specFolder, loopType, sessionId)` namespace. Reusing the same logical ID across independent sessions is allowed because the coverage graph uses a composite key.\n163: \n164: ---\n165: \n166: ## 7. EVENT RECORDS\n167: \n168: Lifecycle event:\n169: \n170: ```json\n171: {\n172:   \"type\": \"event\",\n173:   \"event\": \"resumed\",\n174:   \"mode\": \"research\",\n175:   \"sessionId\": \"dr-2026-05-24T00-00-00Z\",\n176:   \"parentSessionId\": \"dr-2026-05-24T00-00-00Z\",\n177:   \"lineageMode\": \"resume\",\n178:   \"continuedFromRun\": 4,\n179:   \"generation\": 1,\n180:   \"archivedPath\": null,\n181:   \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-24T00:00:00Z\"\n182: }\n183: ```\n184: \n185: Blocked stop event:\n186: \n187: ```json\n188: {\n189:   \"type\": \"event\",\n190:   \"event\": \"blocked_stop\",\n191:   \"mode\": \"research\",\n192:   \"run\": 7,\n193:   \"stopReason\": \"blockedStop\",\n194:   \"blockedBy\": [\"keyQuestionCoverage\", \"sourceDiversity\"],\n195:   \"recoveryStrategy\": \"focus_pivot\",\n196:   \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-24T00:00:00Z\"\n197: }\n198: ```\n199: \n200: Pause event:\n201: \n202: ```json\n203: {\n204:   \"type\": \"event\",\n205:   \"event\": \"userPaused\",\n206:   \"mode\": \"research\",\n207:   \"run\": 7,\n208:   \"stopReason\": \"userPaused\",\n209:   \"sentinelPath\": \"research/.deep-research-pause\",\n210:   \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-24T00:00:00Z\"\n211: }\n212: ```\n213: \n214: Stuck recovery event:\n215: \n216: ```json\n217: {\n218:   \"type\": \"event\",\n219:   \"event\": \"stuckRecovery\",\n220:   \"mode\": \"research\",\n221:   \"run\": 7,\n222:   \"stopReason\": \"stuckRecovery\",\n223:   \"fromFocus\": \"Connection pooling\",\n224:   \"toFocus\": \"Transport alternatives\",\n225:   \"strategy\": \"try_opposites\",\n226:   \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-24T00:00:00Z\"\n227: }\n228: ```\n229: \n230: Graph convergence event shape lives in `../convergence/convergence_graph.md`.\n231: \n232: ---\n233: \n234: ## 8. NORMALIZATION\n235: \n236: Emission-time normalization maps legacy labels into canonical `stopReason` values before persistence. The mapping lives in `../convergence/convergence.md`.\n237: \n238: Malformed lines are handled by the reducer according to its strict/lenient mode. Fault tolerance and reconstruction are documented in `state_reducer_registry.md`.\n\n(End of file - total 238 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: Deep Research JSONL State Reference\ndescription: Config, iteration, event, lineage, graph, and blocked-stop records for deep-research state logs.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"research state jsonl\"\n  - \"research config record\"\n  - \"research iteration records\"\n  - \"research negative knowledge\"\n  - \"research graph events\"\n  - \"research event records\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: implementation\n---\n\n# Deep Research JSONL State Reference\n\n`deep-research-state.jsonl` is append-only. Each line is one JSON object. The first line is normally the config record, followed by iteration and event records.\n\n---\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-research/references/state/state_jsonl.md","text":"---\ntitle: Deep Research JSONL State Reference\ndescription: Config, iteration, event, lineage, graph, and blocked-stop records for deep-research state logs.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"research state jsonl\"\n  - \"research config record\"\n  - \"research iteration records\"\n  - \"research negative knowledge\"\n  - \"research graph events\"\n  - \"research event records\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: implementation\n---\n\n# Deep Research JSONL State Reference\n\n`deep-research-state.jsonl` is append-only. Each line is one JSON object. The first line is normally the config record, followed by iteration and event records.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Purpose\n\nDefine the append-only JSONL records used by deep-research config, iteration, lifecycle, graph, pause, stuck-recovery, and blocked-stop state.\n\n### When to Use\n\nLoad this reference when validating state logs, adding event records, reconstructing a packet, or mapping legacy stop labels to current values.\n\n### Core Principle\n\nRaw JSONL is append-only evidence. Reducer-owned files derive from it, but they do not replace it.\n\n---\n\n## 2. CONFIG RECORD\n\nThe config record captures the initialized loop contract.\n\n```json\n{\n  \"type\": \"config\",\n  \"topic\": \"API response time optimization\",\n  \"maxIterations\": 10,\n  \"convergenceThreshold\": 0.05,\n  \"stuckThreshold\": 3,\n  \"specFolder\": \"028-auto-deep-research\",\n  \"createdAt\": \"2026-05-24T00:00:00Z\"\n}\n```\n\nThe full config file also stores executor, lineage, reducer, capability matrix, pause sentinel, archive, and file-protection settings.\n\n---\n\n## 3. ITERATION RECORDS\n\n```json\n{\n  \"type\": \"iteration\",\n  \"run\": 1,\n  \"status\": \"complete\",\n  \"focus\": \"Initial broad survey\",\n  \"findingsCount\": 5,\n  \"newInfoRatio\": 1.0,\n  \"noveltyJustification\": \"First pass; all findings are new to this packet\",\n  \"keyQuestions\": [\"What causes latency?\"],\n  \"answeredQuestions\": [\"What causes latency?\"],\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-24T00:05:00Z\",\n  \"durationMs\": 45000\n}\n```\n\n| Field | Required | Notes |\n|-------|----------|-------|\n| `type` | Yes | `iteration` |\n| `run` | Yes | 1-indexed iteration number |\n| `status` | Yes | See status values below |\n| `focus` | Yes | Single focus investigated |\n| `findingsCount` | Yes | Number of findings reported |\n| `newInfoRatio` | Yes | Novelty score used by convergence |\n| `noveltyJustification` | Recommended | One-sentence explanation of the ratio |\n| `keyQuestions` | Recommended | Questions considered during this iteration |\n| `answeredQuestions` | Recommended | Questions answered by evidence |\n| `ruledOut` | Optional | Negative knowledge entries |\n| `graphEvents` | Optional | Coverage graph mutations |\n\nStatus values:\n\n| Status | Meaning |\n|--------|---------|\n| `complete` | Normal evidence-gathering iteration |\n| `timeout` | Time/tool budget exceeded |\n| `error` | Tool, parse, or unexpected failure |\n| `stuck` | No new information and no clear next direction |\n| `insight` | Low ratio but important conceptual breakthrough |\n| `thought` | Analytical-only iteration; excluded from stuck and signal math |\n\n---\n\n## 4. CONVERGENCE SIGNAL FIELDS\n\nWhen the composite algorithm runs, the iteration may include signal values:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"type\": \"iteration\",\n  \"run\": 5,\n  \"convergenceSignals\": {\n    \"rollingAvg\": 0.12,\n    \"madScore\": 0.08,\n    \"entropyCoverage\": 0.71,\n    \"compositeStop\": 0.42\n  }\n}\n```\n\nSignal rules live in `../convergence/convergence_signals.md`.\n\n---\n\n## 5. NEGATIVE KNOWLEDGE\n\nUse `ruledOut` to preserve eliminated approaches.\n\n```json\n{\n  \"type\": \"iteration\",\n  \"run\": 3,\n  \"status\": \"complete\",\n  \"ruledOut\": [\n    {\n      \"approach\": \"HTTP/3 multiplexing\",\n      \"reason\": \"No server-side support in target environment\",\n      \"evidence\": \"file:docs/protocols.md:42\"\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\nRuled-out directions should also appear in strategy and synthesis outputs.\n\n---\n\n## 6. GRAPH EVENTS\n\n`graphEvents` records coverage graph mutations from an iteration.\n\n```json\n{\n  \"type\": \"iteration\",\n  \"run\": 4,\n  \"graphEvents\": [\n    {\"type\": \"question\", \"id\": \"q-reconnect\", \"label\": \"How should reconnect work?\"},\n    {\"type\": \"finding\", \"id\": \"f-backoff\", \"label\": \"Exponential backoff is required\"},\n    {\"type\": \"edge\", \"from\": \"f-backoff\", \"to\": \"q-reconnect\", \"relation\": \"ANSWERS\"}\n  ]\n}\n```\n\nValid node types are `question`, `finding`, `claim`, and `source`; `edge` records connect nodes. IDs must be unique within a single `(specFolder, loopType, sessionId)` namespace. Reusing the same logical ID across independent sessions is allowed because the coverage graph uses a composite key.\n\n---\n\n## 7. EVENT RECORDS\n\nLifecycle event:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"type\": \"event\",\n  \"event\": \"resumed\",\n  \"mode\": \"research\",\n  \"sessionId\": \"dr-2026-05-24T00-00-00Z\",\n  \"parentSessionId\": \"dr-2026-05-24T00-00-00Z\",\n  \"lineageMode\": \"resume\",\n  \"continuedFromRun\": 4,\n  \"generation\": 1,\n  \"archivedPath\": null,\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-24T00:00:00Z\"\n}\n```\n\nBlocked stop event:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"type\": \"event\",\n  \"event\": \"blocked_stop\",\n  \"mode\": \"research\",\n  \"run\": 7,\n  \"stopReason\": \"blockedStop\",\n  \"blockedBy\": [\"keyQuestionCoverage\", \"sourceDiversity\"],\n  \"recoveryStrategy\": \"focus_pivot\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-24T00:00:00Z\"\n}\n```\n\nPause event:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"type\": \"event\",\n  \"event\": \"userPaused\",\n  \"mode\": \"research\",\n  \"run\": 7,\n  \"stopReason\": \"userPaused\",\n  \"sentinelPath\": \"research/.deep-research-pause\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-24T00:00:00Z\"\n}\n```\n\nStuck recovery event:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"type\": \"event\",\n  \"event\": \"stuckRecovery\",\n  \"mode\": \"research\",\n  \"run\": 7,\n  \"stopReason\": \"stuckRecovery\",\n  \"fromFocus\": \"Connection pooling\",\n  \"toFocus\": \"Transport alternatives\",\n  \"strategy\": \"try_opposites\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-24T00:00:00Z\"\n}\n```\n\nGraph convergence event shape lives in `../convergence/convergence_graph.md`.\n\n---\n\n## 8. NORMALIZATION\n\nEmission-time normalization maps legacy labels into canonical `stopReason` values before persistence. The mapping lives in `../convergence/convergence.md`.\n\nMalformed lines are handled by the reducer according to its strict/lenient mode. Fault tolerance and reconstruction are documented in `state_reducer_registry.md`.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":238,"totalLines":238,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-research/references/state/state_jsonl.md","time":{"start":1781418094673,"end":1781418094676}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_07f72eb8a7cbf848016a2e486e94088191b4f3a0a97d54d73f"}},"id":"prt_ec4caf04d001MAHcpNqi9r5E0B","sessionID":"ses_13b36ae6fffeLx31BHseD4QV23","messageID":"msg_ec4cad5800011YyuV7QOcYGBmT"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781418094711,"sessionID":"ses_13b36ae6fffeLx31BHseD4QV23","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_XGP2GZBiPKav9Xm5MCGlzcDf","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-research/references/state/state_outputs.md","offset":1,"limit":360},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-research/references/state/state_outputs.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: Deep Research Output Files Reference\n3: description: Markdown output structures for strategy, iterations, dashboard, synthesis, and resource-map artifacts.\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"research output files\"\n6:   - \"research iteration files\"\n7:   - \"research synthesis document\"\n8:   - \"research resource map\"\n9:   - \"research strategy file\"\n10:   - \"spec anchoring output\"\n11: importance_tier: normal\n12: contextType: implementation\n13: ---\n14: \n15: # Deep Research Output Files Reference\n16: \n17: This reference covers human-readable packet outputs. JSONL records live in `state_jsonl.md`; reducer ownership lives in `state_reducer_registry.md`.\n18: \n19: ---\n20: \n21: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n22: \n23: ### Purpose\n24: \n25: Define the human-readable deep-research packet outputs: strategy, iteration markdown, synthesis, dashboard, resource map, and bounded spec anchoring.\n26: \n27: ### When to Use\n28: \n29: Load this reference when writing or validating markdown outputs rather than JSONL records.\n30: \n31: ### Core Principle\n32: \n33: Human-readable outputs must stay synchronized with raw state and respect reducer ownership.\n34: \n35: ---\n36: \n37: ## 2. STRATEGY FILE\n38: \n39: `deep-research-strategy.md` is the persistent research plan. The reducer owns machine-managed sections.\n40: \n41: Required sections:\n42: \n43: - Research Topic\n44: - Known Context\n45: - Key Questions\n46: - Answered Questions\n47: - What Worked\n48: - What Failed\n49: - Exhausted Approaches\n50: - Ruled-Out Directions\n51: - Next Focus\n52: \n53: Update protocol:\n54: \n55: - read strategy before each iteration;\n56: - choose one focus from `Next Focus`;\n57: - append what worked, failed, and was ruled out;\n58: - update answered/open questions through reducer-owned sections;\n59: - when a STOP candidate is blocked, override `Next Focus` with the blocker recovery focus.\n60: \n61: ---\n62: \n63: ## 3. ITERATION FILES\n64: \n65: Iteration files are write-once markdown narratives.\n66: \n67: ```text\n68: research/iterations/iteration-001.md\n69: research/iterations/iteration-002.md\n70: research/iterations/iteration-003.md\n71: ```\n72: \n73: Required shape:\n74: \n75: | Markdown Element | Required Content |\n76: |------------------|------------------|\n77: | H1 title | `Iteration N: Focus Area` |\n78: | `Focus` section | What this iteration investigated |\n79: | `Findings` section | Evidence-backed findings with source citations |\n80: | `Sources Consulted` section | Files, URLs, memory hits, or commands used |\n81: | `Assessment` section | `newInfoRatio`, novelty justification, and confidence notes |\n82: | `Reflection` section | What worked, failed, or was ruled out |\n83: | `Recommended Next Focus` section | One concrete next focus |\n84: \n85: Every finding must cite a source such as `[SOURCE: file:path:line]` or `[SOURCE: https://example.test]`.\n86: \n87: ---\n88: \n89: ## 4. RESEARCH SYNTHESIS\n90: \n91: `research.md` is the workflow-owned synthesis output at `{artifact_dir}/research.md`.\n92: \n93: Rules:\n94: \n95: - progressive synthesis may update the file during the loop;\n96: - final synthesis consolidates duplicate findings and unresolved gaps;\n97: - prior findings are not silently overwritten;\n98: - generated or machine-owned sections must be marked explicitly when the workflow uses them;\n99: - when `resource_map_present` is true, cite `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` in References.\n100: \n101: ---\n102: \n103: ## 5. DASHBOARD\n104: \n105: `deep-research-dashboard.md` is auto-generated from JSONL, strategy, and registry state.\n106: \n107: Expected sections:\n108: \n109: | Section | Source |\n110: |---------|--------|\n111: | Iteration Table | JSONL iteration records |\n112: | Question Status | Strategy + registry |\n113: | Convergence Trend | `convergenceSignals` + reducer |\n114: | Dead Ends | JSONL `ruledOut` + strategy |\n115: | Blocked Stops | Registry blocked-stop history |\n116: | Graph Convergence | Graph convergence registry fields |\n117: | Next Focus | Strategy |\n118: \n119: Generation rules:\n120: \n121: - regenerate after each iteration evaluation;\n122: - compute derived values from raw state;\n123: - overwrite the full dashboard rather than appending;\n124: - if state is missing, write a minimal \"No iteration data available\" dashboard;\n125: - agent writes are discarded on next refresh.\n126: \n127: ---\n128: \n129: ## 6. RESOURCE MAP\n130: \n131: When `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` exists at init:\n132: \n133: - persist `resource_map_present: true` in config;\n134: - summarize section counts and themes into strategy `Known Context`;\n135: - treat listed files as known inventory, not net-new discoveries;\n136: - cite the map in final synthesis references;\n137: - emit `{artifact_dir}/resource-map.md` from converged deltas unless disabled.\n138: \n139: When absent:\n140: \n141: - persist `resource_map_present: false`;\n142: - write `resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate` into `Known Context`;\n143: - continue normally.\n144: \n145: ---\n146: \n147: ## 7. SPEC ANCHORING OUTPUT\n148: \n149: `references/protocol/spec_check_protocol.md` defines bounded `spec.md` writes:\n150: \n151: - acquire `research/.deep-research.lock`;\n152: - classify `folder_state`;\n153: - seed or append bounded context during init when allowed;\n154: - replace exactly one generated findings fence during synthesis.\n155: \n156: This output path is protocol-owned, not iteration-agent owned.\n\n(End of file - total 156 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: Deep Research Output Files Reference\ndescription: Markdown output structures for strategy, iterations, dashboard, synthesis, and resource-map artifacts.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"research output files\"\n  - \"research iteration files\"\n  - \"research synthesis document\"\n  - \"research resource map\"\n  - \"research strategy file\"\n  - \"spec anchoring output\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: implementation\n---\n\n# Deep Research Output Files Reference\n\nThis reference covers human-readable packet outputs. JSONL records live in `state_jsonl.md`; reducer ownership lives in `state_reducer_registry.md`.\n\n---\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-research/references/state/state_outputs.md","text":"---\ntitle: Deep Research Output Files Reference\ndescription: Markdown output structures for strategy, iterations, dashboard, synthesis, and resource-map artifacts.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"research output files\"\n  - \"research iteration files\"\n  - \"research synthesis document\"\n  - \"research resource map\"\n  - \"research strategy file\"\n  - \"spec anchoring output\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: implementation\n---\n\n# Deep Research Output Files Reference\n\nThis reference covers human-readable packet outputs. JSONL records live in `state_jsonl.md`; reducer ownership lives in `state_reducer_registry.md`.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Purpose\n\nDefine the human-readable deep-research packet outputs: strategy, iteration markdown, synthesis, dashboard, resource map, and bounded spec anchoring.\n\n### When to Use\n\nLoad this reference when writing or validating markdown outputs rather than JSONL records.\n\n### Core Principle\n\nHuman-readable outputs must stay synchronized with raw state and respect reducer ownership.\n\n---\n\n## 2. STRATEGY FILE\n\n`deep-research-strategy.md` is the persistent research plan. The reducer owns machine-managed sections.\n\nRequired sections:\n\n- Research Topic\n- Known Context\n- Key Questions\n- Answered Questions\n- What Worked\n- What Failed\n- Exhausted Approaches\n- Ruled-Out Directions\n- Next Focus\n\nUpdate protocol:\n\n- read strategy before each iteration;\n- choose one focus from `Next Focus`;\n- append what worked, failed, and was ruled out;\n- update answered/open questions through reducer-owned sections;\n- when a STOP candidate is blocked, override `Next Focus` with the blocker recovery focus.\n\n---\n\n## 3. ITERATION FILES\n\nIteration files are write-once markdown narratives.\n\n```text\nresearch/iterations/iteration-001.md\nresearch/iterations/iteration-002.md\nresearch/iterations/iteration-003.md\n```\n\nRequired shape:\n\n| Markdown Element | Required Content |\n|------------------|------------------|\n| H1 title | `Iteration N: Focus Area` |\n| `Focus` section | What this iteration investigated |\n| `Findings` section | Evidence-backed findings with source citations |\n| `Sources Consulted` section | Files, URLs, memory hits, or commands used |\n| `Assessment` section | `newInfoRatio`, novelty justification, and confidence notes |\n| `Reflection` section | What worked, failed, or was ruled out |\n| `Recommended Next Focus` section | One concrete next focus |\n\nEvery finding must cite a source such as `[SOURCE: file:path:line]` or `[SOURCE: https://example.test]`.\n\n---\n\n## 4. RESEARCH SYNTHESIS\n\n`research.md` is the workflow-owned synthesis output at `{artifact_dir}/research.md`.\n\nRules:\n\n- progressive synthesis may update the file during the loop;\n- final synthesis consolidates duplicate findings and unresolved gaps;\n- prior findings are not silently overwritten;\n- generated or machine-owned sections must be marked explicitly when the workflow uses them;\n- when `resource_map_present` is true, cite `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` in References.\n\n---\n\n## 5. DASHBOARD\n\n`deep-research-dashboard.md` is auto-generated from JSONL, strategy, and registry state.\n\nExpected sections:\n\n| Section | Source |\n|---------|--------|\n| Iteration Table | JSONL iteration records |\n| Question Status | Strategy + registry |\n| Convergence Trend | `convergenceSignals` + reducer |\n| Dead Ends | JSONL `ruledOut` + strategy |\n| Blocked Stops | Registry blocked-stop history |\n| Graph Convergence | Graph convergence registry fields |\n| Next Focus | Strategy |\n\nGeneration rules:\n\n- regenerate after each iteration evaluation;\n- compute derived values from raw state;\n- overwrite the full dashboard rather than appending;\n- if state is missing, write a minimal \"No iteration data available\" dashboard;\n- agent writes are discarded on next refresh.\n\n---\n\n## 6. RESOURCE MAP\n\nWhen `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` exists at init:\n\n- persist `resource_map_present: true` in config;\n- summarize section counts and themes into strategy `Known Context`;\n- treat listed files as known inventory, not net-new discoveries;\n- cite the map in final synthesis references;\n- emit `{artifact_dir}/resource-map.md` from converged deltas unless disabled.\n\nWhen absent:\n\n- persist `resource_map_present: false`;\n- write `resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate` into `Known Context`;\n- continue normally.\n\n---\n\n## 7. SPEC ANCHORING OUTPUT\n\n`references/protocol/spec_check_protocol.md` defines bounded `spec.md` writes:\n\n- acquire `research/.deep-research.lock`;\n- classify `folder_state`;\n- seed or append bounded context during init when allowed;\n- replace exactly one generated findings fence during synthesis.\n\nThis output path is protocol-owned, not iteration-agent owned.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":156,"totalLines":156,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-research/references/state/state_outputs.md","time":{"start":1781418094705,"end":1781418094711}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_07f72eb8a7cbf848016a2e486e94108191bb3f70c3004ef2c5"}},"id":"prt_ec4caf0620016FM4B3WssWu2qa","sessionID":"ses_13b36ae6fffeLx31BHseD4QV23","messageID":"msg_ec4cad5800011YyuV7QOcYGBmT"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781418094719,"sessionID":"ses_13b36ae6fffeLx31BHseD4QV23","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_kTwj8D04mcx03RbOKj1fvrc8","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_start-research-loop_auto.yaml","offset":1,"limit":300},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_start-research-loop_auto.yaml</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n2: # DEEP RESEARCH: AUTONOMOUS DEEP RESEARCH LOOP (AUTO MODE)\n3: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n4: # YAML PREDICATE GRAMMAR CONTRACT (S7 / M11):\n5: # - This asset does not currently use typed BooleanExpr predicates under\n6: #   `when:`; flow control is branch-label-driven (`on_resume`, `on_fresh`,\n7: #   `on_restart`, etc.). Retain the existing shape.\n8: # - `after:` carries prose timing / narrative notes if needed; `when:` in\n9: #   this file is reserved for future typed predicates and must NOT carry\n10: #   free-form narrative prose.\n11: # - See `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/predicates/boolean-expr.ts`\n12: #   for the canonical BooleanExpr grammar.\n13: #\n14: # GATE 3 CLASSIFICATION (T-YML-DPR-01 / paired with T-DOC-03 R50-001):\n15: # - `resume` is a tested WRITE-PATH that produces `iteration-NNN.md` files\n16: #   and JSONL state-log appends. The workflow classifies resume as\n17: #   write-path below (see `gate3_classification` fields) so Gate 3 trigger\n18: #   extraction can surface resume correctly rather than false-negative.\n19: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n20: role: Deep Research Loop Manager\n21: purpose: Iterative deep research with convergence detection\n22: action: Run deep-research loop from initialization through synthesis\n23: operating_mode:\n24:   workflow: iterative_loop\n25:   workflow_compliance: MANDATORY\n26:   workflow_execution: autonomous\n27:   approvals: none\n28:   tracking: progressive_research_state\n29:   validation: convergence_detection\n30: \n31: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n32: # OPERATING PRINCIPLES\n33: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n34: operating_principles:\n35:   core: \"Fresh context per iteration + externalized state = no context degradation\"\n36:   approach: \"Dispatch focused agent, evaluate convergence, repeat or stop\"\n37:   mandate: \"Never hold findings in memory; write everything to files\"\n38: \n39: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n40: # USER INPUTS (from setup phase)\n41: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n42: user_inputs:\n43:   research_topic: \"[RESEARCH_TOPIC] - Topic to investigate deeply. REQUIRED.\"\n44:   spec_folder: \"[SPEC_FOLDER] - Spec folder path. REQUIRED.\"\n45:   max_iterations: \"[MAX_ITERATIONS] - Maximum loop iterations. Default: 10.\"\n46:   convergence_threshold: \"[CONVERGENCE_THRESHOLD] - Stop threshold. Default: 0.05.\"\n47: \n48: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n49: # CONTEXT LOADING\n50: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n51: context_loading:\n52:   trigger: \"At workflow START, before phase_init\"\n53:   purpose: \"Load prior research context for the topic and buffer it until strategy.md exists\"\n54:   mcp_integration:\n55:     tool: memory_context\n56:     note: \"Call MCP tools directly - NEVER through Code Mode\"\n57:     parameters: { input: \"{research_topic}\", mode: \"focused\", intent: \"understand\", includeContent: true }\n58:   when_to_skip: [\"User says 'skip context' or 'fresh start'\"]\n59:   behavior:\n60:     if_context_found: \"Store full results as prior_context plus a concise prior_context_summary; inject after strategy.md is created.\"\n61:     if_no_context: \"Set prior_context and prior_context_summary to 'None' and continue.\"\n62: \n63: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n64: # SKILL REFERENCE\n65: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n66: skill_reference:\n67:   skill: deep-research\n68:   skill_md: .opencode/skills/deep-research/SKILL.md\n69:   references:\n70:     loop_protocol: .opencode/skills/deep-research/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md\n71:     spec_check_protocol: .opencode/skills/deep-research/references/protocol/spec_check_protocol.md\n72:     state_format: .opencode/skills/deep-research/references/state/state_format.md\n73:     convergence: .opencode/skills/deep-research/references/convergence/convergence.md\n74:   templates:\n75:     config: .opencode/skills/deep-research/assets/deep_research_config.json\n76:     strategy: .opencode/skills/deep-research/assets/deep_research_strategy.md\n77: \n78: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n79: # AGENT CONFIGURATION\n80: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n81: agent_config:\n82:   agent: deep-research\n83:   agent_file: \".opencode/agents/deep-research.md\"\n84:   # Canonical path. Runtime-specific directories (e.g. .claude/agents/) reference this source.\n85:   model: opus\n86:   leaf_only: true\n87:   tools: [Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Grep, Glob, WebFetch]\n88:   mcp_servers: [mk-spec-memory]\n89:   tool_call_budget: { target: 8, max: 12 }\n90: \n91: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n92: # STATE FILE PATHS\n93: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n94: state_paths:\n95:   # Template paths document the canonical packet layout. Runtime resolution happens via\n96:   # step_resolve_artifact_root plus the shared resolver, so root specs keep root-local\n97:   # research/ and child phases keep local research/ packet directories.\n98:   packet_dir: \"{artifact_dir}\"\n99:   config: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-research-config.json\"\n100:   state_log: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-research-state.jsonl\"\n101:   strategy: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-research-strategy.md\"\n102:   registry: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-research-findings-registry.json\"\n103:   dashboard: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-research-dashboard.md\"\n104:   pause_sentinel: \"{artifact_dir}/.deep-research-pause\"\n105:   lock_file: \"{artifact_dir}/.deep-research.lock\"\n106:   prompt_dir: \"{artifact_dir}/prompts\"\n107:   iteration_dir: \"{artifact_dir}/iterations\"\n108:   iteration_pattern: \"{artifact_dir}/iterations/iteration-{NNN}.md\"\n109:   # Per-iteration structured delta stream (one file per iteration) — complement to the\n110:   # canonical state_log append. The delta file MUST contain at least one record whose\n111:   # `type === \"iteration\"` so the reducer can rehydrate iteration state after a partial\n112:   # run. Variants like `\"iteration_delta\"` are silently dropped by the reducer; the\n113:   # post_dispatch_validate step enforces the canonical type below.\n114:   delta_dir: \"{artifact_dir}/deltas\"\n115:   delta_pattern: \"{artifact_dir}/deltas/iter-{NNN}.jsonl\"\n116:   research_output: \"{artifact_dir}/research.md\"\n117:   resource_map_output: \"{artifact_dir}/resource-map.md\"\n118:   archive_root: \"{artifact_archive_root}\"\n119:   synthesis_snapshot_pattern: \"{artifact_dir}/synthesis-v{generation}.md\"\n120: \n121: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n122: # WORKFLOW\n123: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n124: workflow:\n125: \n126:   step_resolve_artifact_root:\n127:     description: \"Resolve artifact directory — use fan-out lineage override when provided, else resolve from spec_folder\"\n128:     note: \"Root specs keep research artifacts directly in {spec_folder}/research/. Child phases and sub-phases keep local packet directories in {spec_folder}/research/{packet}/, and archives stay local at {spec_folder}/research_archive/{packet}/.\"\n129:     branch_on: \"config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir\"\n130:     if_present:\n131:       bind:\n132:         artifact_dir: \"{config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir}\"\n133:         artifact_root_dir: \"{config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir}\"\n134:         artifact_subfolder: null\n135:         artifact_archive_root: \"{config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir}/_archive\"\n136:     if_absent:\n137:       command: \"node -e \\\"const { resolveArtifactRoot } = require('.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/review-research-paths.cjs'); console.log(JSON.stringify(resolveArtifactRoot('{spec_folder}', 'research')));\\\"\"\n138:       outputs:\n139:         - artifact_root_dir: \"Resolved local research owner directory\"\n140:         - artifact_subfolder: \"Local packet subfolder ({ownerSlug}-pt-{NN}), else null\"\n141:         - artifact_dir: \"Resolved research packet directory for this target\"\n142:         - artifact_archive_root: \"Resolved local research archive directory for this target\"\n143: \n144:   step_fanout_spawn:\n145:     description: \"Spawn fan-out lineages; skip and proceed to phase_init normally when single-executor\"\n146:     skip_when: \"config.fanout is absent\"\n147:     instructions: |\n148:       Fan-out mode is active. Spawn all lineages. Each lineage runs the full loop in its own\n149:       isolated sub-packet under {artifact_dir}/lineages/{label}/.\n150:       After all lineages complete, jump directly to phase_synthesis — skip phase_init and\n151:       phase_main_loop entirely (those are the single-executor path). The merge step in\n152:       phase_synthesis will consolidate results across all lineages.\n153:     sub_steps:\n154:       step_fanout_spawn_cli:\n155:         description: \"Spawn all CLI lineages in capped worker pool\"\n156:         skip_when: \"no entries in config.fanout.executors with kind != 'native'\"\n157:         command: |\n158:           node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs \\\n159:             --spec-folder {spec_folder} \\\n160:             --loop-type research \\\n161:             --fanout-config-json '{config.fanout_json}' \\\n162:             --base-artifact-dir {artifact_dir}\n163:         working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n164:         wait_for_completion: true\n165:       step_fanout_spawn_native:\n166:         description: \"Dispatch each native lineage as a sequential deep-research sub-agent\"\n167:         skip_when: \"no entries in config.fanout.executors with kind == 'native'\"\n168:         for_each: \"lineage in expanded native entries of config.fanout\"\n169:         dispatch:\n170:           agent: deep-research\n171:           model: opus\n172:           context: |\n173:             Execute the deep-research loop with these parameters:\n174:               spec_folder: {spec_folder}\n175:               config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir: {artifact_dir}/lineages/{lineage.label}\n176:               session_id: fanout-{lineage.label}-{fanout_run_id}\n177:               executor: native\n178:             Run to convergence. Write all outputs to the override directory.\n179:         wait_for_completion: true\n180: \n181:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n182:   # PHASE 1: INITIALIZATION\n183:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n184:   phase_init:\n185:     purpose: Create all state files for the research session\n186:     steps:\n187: \n188:       step_preflight_contract:\n189:         action: \"Validate required setup bindings and executable workflow contract before any file writes\"\n190:         verify:\n191:           - required_values_present: [research_topic, spec_folder, max_iterations, convergence_threshold]\n192:           - spec_folder_is_within: \"specs/ or .opencode/specs/ (canonicalize alias roots before validation)\"\n193:           - unresolved_placeholders: \"FAIL if any user-facing template references placeholders not produced by earlier steps\"\n194:           - tool_contract: \"FAIL if executable steps reference tools outside the command allowlist\"\n195:         on_fail: \"Halt with STATUS=FAIL and report the missing binding or unsupported contract reference\"\n196: \n197:       step_create_directories:\n198:         action: \"Create spec folder and research packet directories if they don't exist\"\n199:         command: \"mkdir -p {state_paths.prompt_dir} {state_paths.iteration_dir} {state_paths.delta_dir}\"\n200: \n201:       step_detect_resource_map:\n202:         action: \"Detect resource-map.md before config creation so init can persist the flag and seed Known Context\"\n203:         inspect:\n204:           - \"{spec_folder}/resource-map.md\"\n205:         classify:\n206:           present: \"resource-map.md exists at init\"\n207:           absent: \"resource-map.md does not exist at init\"\n208:         outputs:\n209:           - resource_map_present: \"Boolean true when {spec_folder}/resource-map.md exists, else false\"\n210:           - resource_map_known_context: \"When present: summarize the map by section with entry counts across READMEs, Documents, Commands, Agents, Skills, Specs, Scripts, Tests, Config, and Meta, plus a one-line theme summary for each section. When absent: 'resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate'.\"\n211: \n212:       step_resolve_canonical_names:\n213:         action: \"Resolve canonical research packet artifact names before classification\"\n214:         inspect_legacy:\n215:           - \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/config.json\"\n216:           - \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/state.jsonl\"\n217:           - \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/strategy.md\"\n218:           - \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/dashboard.md\"\n219:           - \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/.pause\"\n220:         migration_policy: \"dual-read / single-write for 4 weeks\"\n221:         on_legacy_read:\n222:           append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"migration\",\"legacyPath\":\"{legacy_path}\",\"canonicalPath\":\"{canonical_path}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n223: \n224:       step_acquire_lock:\n225:         action: \"Acquire the advisory lock defined by the spec_check_protocol before session classification\"\n226:         command: \"Open {state_paths.lock_file} with exclusive non-blocking advisory locking semantics; fail closed on contention.\"\n227:         note: \"macOS/BSD locking here is advisory. Stale-lock override is confirm-only or explicit recovery-only.\"\n228:         # <!-- F-010-B5-01 -->\n229:         # Lock-cleanup contract: the lock file MUST be released on every terminal exit path that follows acquisition.\n230:         # Runtimes honoring step_acquire_lock are required to perform this cleanup before halting or pausing.\n231:         on_halt:\n232:           action: \"Release {state_paths.lock_file} before any terminal halt branch returns control\"\n233:           applies_to: [\"step_classify_session.on_invalid_state\", \"step_classify_session.on_completed_session\", \"step_preinit_spec_branch.conflict-detected\"]\n234:           command: \"Remove or close-with-release {state_paths.lock_file}; failures here are logged but do not block the halt\"\n235:         on_cancel:\n236:           action: \"Release {state_paths.lock_file} on user cancel or pause-sentinel detection before sentinel processing\"\n237:           command: \"Remove or close-with-release {state_paths.lock_file}; cancel completes regardless of cleanup result\"\n238:         on_workflow_exit:\n239:           action: \"Release {state_paths.lock_file} as the final step of any workflow exit path (success or failure)\"\n240:           command: \"Remove or close-with-release {state_paths.lock_file}; idempotent — safe to invoke when already released\"\n241: \n242:       step_classify_session:\n243:         action: \"Classify the session before writing files\"\n244:         inspect:\n245:           - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n246:           - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n247:           - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n248:         classify:\n249:           fresh: \"None of the three state artifacts exist\"\n250:           resume: \"Config, JSONL, and strategy all exist and agree on topic/spec folder\"\n251:           completed-session: \"Resume artifacts exist and config.status == 'complete'\"\n252:           invalid-state: \"Any partial, missing, or contradictory combination\"\n253:         outputs:\n254:           - session_state: \"fresh | resume | completed-session | invalid-state\"\n255:         on_resume:\n256:           # T-YML-DPR-01 / R50-001: Resume is a WRITE-PATH. Produces `iteration-NNN.md` + JSONL appends.\n257:           # Paired with T-DOC-03 Gate 3 trigger addition (resume, save context, save memory, /memory:save).\n258:           gate3_classification: write-path\n259:           gate3_rationale: \"resume produces iteration-NNN.md writes and JSONL state-log appends\"\n260:           log: \"Auto-resume: state artifacts are complete and consistent. Continue the same lineage (sessionId unchanged, generation unchanged, no archive).\"\n261:           append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"resumed\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"parentSessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"lineageMode\":\"resume\",\"continuedFromRun\":{iteration_count},\"generation\":{generation},\"archivedPath\":null,\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n262:           skip_to: phase_loop\n263:         on_restart:\n264:           action: \"Archive the current research packet under the root-level research_archive/ tree and start a new lineage segment with a fresh sessionId and generation+1.\"\n265:           command: \"if [ -d {state_paths.packet_dir} ]; then mkdir -p {state_paths.archive_root} && mv {state_paths.packet_dir} {state_paths.archive_root}/{timestamp_slug}; fi\"\n266:           set:\n267:             lineage_mode: \"restart\"\n268:             parent_session_id: \"{prior_session_id}\"\n269:             generation: \"{prior_generation + 1}\"\n270:           append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"restarted\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"parentSessionId\":\"{prior_session_id}\",\"lineageMode\":\"restart\",\"generation\":{generation},\"archivedPath\":\"{state_paths.archive_root}/{timestamp_slug}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n271:           skip_to: step_create_config\n272:         note_deferred_branches: \"fork and completed-continue are deferred and no longer runtime-supported in this release. The reducer still reads `lineageMode` from config for dashboards and analysis, but only `new`, `resume`, and `restart` are live. See deep-research/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md §Lifecycle Branch Contract for the one-session contract.\"\n273:         on_completed_session:\n274:           log: \"Prior session already completed. Do not route directly to synthesis; archive the completed research/ tree or start a fresh packet instead.\"\n275:           halt: true\n276:           message: \"Completed deep-research packet detected. Archive or replace the existing research/ tree before starting a new session.\"\n277:         on_invalid_state:\n278:           halt: true\n279:           message: \"Existing deep-research state is incomplete or contradictory. Repair or archive the invalid research packet before continuing.\"\n280:         on_fresh:\n281:           action: \"Proceed with a new session\"\n282: \n283:       step_create_config:\n284:         action: \"Create deep-research-config.json from template\"\n285:         template: .opencode/skills/deep-research/assets/deep_research_config.json\n286:         populate:\n287:           topic: \"{research_topic}\"\n288:           maxIterations: \"{max_iterations}\"\n289:           # Semantic: newInfoRatio with negative-knowledge emphasis. See SKILL.md §\"Convergence Threshold Semantics\".\n290:           convergenceThreshold: \"{convergence_threshold}\"\n291:           stuckThreshold: 3\n292:           maxDurationMinutes: 120\n293:           specFolder: \"{spec_folder}\"\n294:           resource_map_present: \"{resource_map_present}\"\n295:           # <!-- F-010-B5-04 -->\n296:           # Honor the parsed --no-resource-map flag from deep-research.md:73 (default true; false when flag is set).\n297:           # The markdown command parses $ARGUMENTS and binds {resource_map_emit} before this step runs.\n298:           resource_map.emit: \"{resource_map_emit}\"\n299:           createdAt: \"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"\n300:           status: \"initialized\"\n\n(Showing lines 1-300 of 1079. Use offset=301 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# DEEP RESEARCH: AUTONOMOUS DEEP RESEARCH LOOP (AUTO MODE)\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# YAML PREDICATE GRAMMAR CONTRACT (S7 / M11):\n# - This asset does not currently use typed BooleanExpr predicates under\n#   `when:`; flow control is branch-label-driven (`on_resume`, `on_fresh`,\n#   `on_restart`, etc.). Retain the existing shape.\n# - `after:` carries prose timing / narrative notes if needed; `when:` in\n#   this file is reserved for future typed predicates and must NOT carry\n#   free-form narrative prose.\n# - See `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/predicates/boolean-expr.ts`\n#   for the canonical BooleanExpr grammar.\n#\n# GATE 3 CLASSIFICATION (T-YML-DPR-01 / paired with T-DOC-03 R50-001):\n# - `resume` is a tested WRITE-PATH that produces `iteration-NNN.md` files\n#   and JSONL state-log appends. The workflow classifies resume as\n#   write-path below (see `gate3_classification` fields) so Gate 3 trigger\n#   extraction can surface resume correctly rather than false-negative.\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nrole: Deep Research Loop Manager","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_start-research-loop_auto.yaml","text":"# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# DEEP RESEARCH: AUTONOMOUS DEEP RESEARCH LOOP (AUTO MODE)\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# YAML PREDICATE GRAMMAR CONTRACT (S7 / M11):\n# - This asset does not currently use typed BooleanExpr predicates under\n#   `when:`; flow control is branch-label-driven (`on_resume`, `on_fresh`,\n#   `on_restart`, etc.). Retain the existing shape.\n# - `after:` carries prose timing / narrative notes if needed; `when:` in\n#   this file is reserved for future typed predicates and must NOT carry\n#   free-form narrative prose.\n# - See `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/predicates/boolean-expr.ts`\n#   for the canonical BooleanExpr grammar.\n#\n# GATE 3 CLASSIFICATION (T-YML-DPR-01 / paired with T-DOC-03 R50-001):\n# - `resume` is a tested WRITE-PATH that produces `iteration-NNN.md` files\n#   and JSONL state-log appends. The workflow classifies resume as\n#   write-path below (see `gate3_classification` fields) so Gate 3 trigger\n#   extraction can surface resume correctly rather than false-negative.\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nrole: Deep Research Loop Manager\npurpose: Iterative deep research with convergence detection\naction: Run deep-research loop from initialization through synthesis\noperating_mode:\n  workflow: iterative_loop\n  workflow_compliance: MANDATORY\n  workflow_execution: autonomous\n  approvals: none\n  tracking: progressive_research_state\n  validation: convergence_detection\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# OPERATING PRINCIPLES\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\noperating_principles:\n  core: \"Fresh context per iteration + externalized state = no context degradation\"\n  approach: \"Dispatch focused agent, evaluate convergence, repeat or stop\"\n  mandate: \"Never hold findings in memory; write everything to files\"\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# USER INPUTS (from setup phase)\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nuser_inputs:\n  research_topic: \"[RESEARCH_TOPIC] - Topic to investigate deeply. REQUIRED.\"\n  spec_folder: \"[SPEC_FOLDER] - Spec folder path. REQUIRED.\"\n  max_iterations: \"[MAX_ITERATIONS] - Maximum loop iterations. Default: 10.\"\n  convergence_threshold: \"[CONVERGENCE_THRESHOLD] - Stop threshold. Default: 0.05.\"\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# CONTEXT LOADING\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\ncontext_loading:\n  trigger: \"At workflow START, before phase_init\"\n  purpose: \"Load prior research context for the topic and buffer it until strategy.md exists\"\n  mcp_integration:\n    tool: memory_context\n    note: \"Call MCP tools directly - NEVER through Code Mode\"\n    parameters: { input: \"{research_topic}\", mode: \"focused\", intent: \"understand\", includeContent: true }\n  when_to_skip: [\"User says 'skip context' or 'fresh start'\"]\n  behavior:\n    if_context_found: \"Store full results as prior_context plus a concise prior_context_summary; inject after strategy.md is created.\"\n    if_no_context: \"Set prior_context and prior_context_summary to 'None' and continue.\"\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# SKILL REFERENCE\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nskill_reference:\n  skill: deep-research\n  skill_md: .opencode/skills/deep-research/SKILL.md\n  references:\n    loop_protocol: .opencode/skills/deep-research/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md\n    spec_check_protocol: .opencode/skills/deep-research/references/protocol/spec_check_protocol.md\n    state_format: .opencode/skills/deep-research/references/state/state_format.md\n    convergence: .opencode/skills/deep-research/references/convergence/convergence.md\n  templates:\n    config: .opencode/skills/deep-research/assets/deep_research_config.json\n    strategy: .opencode/skills/deep-research/assets/deep_research_strategy.md\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# AGENT CONFIGURATION\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nagent_config:\n  agent: deep-research\n  agent_file: \".opencode/agents/deep-research.md\"\n  # Canonical path. Runtime-specific directories (e.g. .claude/agents/) reference this source.\n  model: opus\n  leaf_only: true\n  tools: [Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Grep, Glob, WebFetch]\n  mcp_servers: [mk-spec-memory]\n  tool_call_budget: { target: 8, max: 12 }\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# STATE FILE PATHS\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nstate_paths:\n  # Template paths document the canonical packet layout. Runtime resolution happens via\n  # step_resolve_artifact_root plus the shared resolver, so root specs keep root-local\n  # research/ and child phases keep local research/ packet directories.\n  packet_dir: \"{artifact_dir}\"\n  config: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-research-config.json\"\n  state_log: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-research-state.jsonl\"\n  strategy: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-research-strategy.md\"\n  registry: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-research-findings-registry.json\"\n  dashboard: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-research-dashboard.md\"\n  pause_sentinel: \"{artifact_dir}/.deep-research-pause\"\n  lock_file: \"{artifact_dir}/.deep-research.lock\"\n  prompt_dir: \"{artifact_dir}/prompts\"\n  iteration_dir: \"{artifact_dir}/iterations\"\n  iteration_pattern: \"{artifact_dir}/iterations/iteration-{NNN}.md\"\n  # Per-iteration structured delta stream (one file per iteration) — complement to the\n  # canonical state_log append. The delta file MUST contain at least one record whose\n  # `type === \"iteration\"` so the reducer can rehydrate iteration state after a partial\n  # run. Variants like `\"iteration_delta\"` are silently dropped by the reducer; the\n  # post_dispatch_validate step enforces the canonical type below.\n  delta_dir: \"{artifact_dir}/deltas\"\n  delta_pattern: \"{artifact_dir}/deltas/iter-{NNN}.jsonl\"\n  research_output: \"{artifact_dir}/research.md\"\n  resource_map_output: \"{artifact_dir}/resource-map.md\"\n  archive_root: \"{artifact_archive_root}\"\n  synthesis_snapshot_pattern: \"{artifact_dir}/synthesis-v{generation}.md\"\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# WORKFLOW\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nworkflow:\n\n  step_resolve_artifact_root:\n    description: \"Resolve artifact directory — use fan-out lineage override when provided, else resolve from spec_folder\"\n    note: \"Root specs keep research artifacts directly in {spec_folder}/research/. Child phases and sub-phases keep local packet directories in {spec_folder}/research/{packet}/, and archives stay local at {spec_folder}/research_archive/{packet}/.\"\n    branch_on: \"config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir\"\n    if_present:\n      bind:\n        artifact_dir: \"{config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir}\"\n        artifact_root_dir: \"{config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir}\"\n        artifact_subfolder: null\n        artifact_archive_root: \"{config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir}/_archive\"\n    if_absent:\n      command: \"node -e \\\"const { resolveArtifactRoot } = require('.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/review-research-paths.cjs'); console.log(JSON.stringify(resolveArtifactRoot('{spec_folder}', 'research')));\\\"\"\n      outputs:\n        - artifact_root_dir: \"Resolved local research owner directory\"\n        - artifact_subfolder: \"Local packet subfolder ({ownerSlug}-pt-{NN}), else null\"\n        - artifact_dir: \"Resolved research packet directory for this target\"\n        - artifact_archive_root: \"Resolved local research archive directory for this target\"\n\n  step_fanout_spawn:\n    description: \"Spawn fan-out lineages; skip and proceed to phase_init normally when single-executor\"\n    skip_when: \"config.fanout is absent\"\n    instructions: |\n      Fan-out mode is active. Spawn all lineages. Each lineage runs the full loop in its own\n      isolated sub-packet under {artifact_dir}/lineages/{label}/.\n      After all lineages complete, jump directly to phase_synthesis — skip phase_init and\n      phase_main_loop entirely (those are the single-executor path). The merge step in\n      phase_synthesis will consolidate results across all lineages.\n    sub_steps:\n      step_fanout_spawn_cli:\n        description: \"Spawn all CLI lineages in capped worker pool\"\n        skip_when: \"no entries in config.fanout.executors with kind != 'native'\"\n        command: |\n          node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs \\\n            --spec-folder {spec_folder} \\\n            --loop-type research \\\n            --fanout-config-json '{config.fanout_json}' \\\n            --base-artifact-dir {artifact_dir}\n        working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n        wait_for_completion: true\n      step_fanout_spawn_native:\n        description: \"Dispatch each native lineage as a sequential deep-research sub-agent\"\n        skip_when: \"no entries in config.fanout.executors with kind == 'native'\"\n        for_each: \"lineage in expanded native entries of config.fanout\"\n        dispatch:\n          agent: deep-research\n          model: opus\n          context: |\n            Execute the deep-research loop with these parameters:\n              spec_folder: {spec_folder}\n              config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir: {artifact_dir}/lineages/{lineage.label}\n              session_id: fanout-{lineage.label}-{fanout_run_id}\n              executor: native\n            Run to convergence. Write all outputs to the override directory.\n        wait_for_completion: true\n\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  # PHASE 1: INITIALIZATION\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  phase_init:\n    purpose: Create all state files for the research session\n    steps:\n\n      step_preflight_contract:\n        action: \"Validate required setup bindings and executable workflow contract before any file writes\"\n        verify:\n          - required_values_present: [research_topic, spec_folder, max_iterations, convergence_threshold]\n          - spec_folder_is_within: \"specs/ or .opencode/specs/ (canonicalize alias roots before validation)\"\n          - unresolved_placeholders: \"FAIL if any user-facing template references placeholders not produced by earlier steps\"\n          - tool_contract: \"FAIL if executable steps reference tools outside the command allowlist\"\n        on_fail: \"Halt with STATUS=FAIL and report the missing binding or unsupported contract reference\"\n\n      step_create_directories:\n        action: \"Create spec folder and research packet directories if they don't exist\"\n        command: \"mkdir -p {state_paths.prompt_dir} {state_paths.iteration_dir} {state_paths.delta_dir}\"\n\n      step_detect_resource_map:\n        action: \"Detect resource-map.md before config creation so init can persist the flag and seed Known Context\"\n        inspect:\n          - \"{spec_folder}/resource-map.md\"\n        classify:\n          present: \"resource-map.md exists at init\"\n          absent: \"resource-map.md does not exist at init\"\n        outputs:\n          - resource_map_present: \"Boolean true when {spec_folder}/resource-map.md exists, else false\"\n          - resource_map_known_context: \"When present: summarize the map by section with entry counts across READMEs, Documents, Commands, Agents, Skills, Specs, Scripts, Tests, Config, and Meta, plus a one-line theme summary for each section. When absent: 'resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate'.\"\n\n      step_resolve_canonical_names:\n        action: \"Resolve canonical research packet artifact names before classification\"\n        inspect_legacy:\n          - \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/config.json\"\n          - \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/state.jsonl\"\n          - \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/strategy.md\"\n          - \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/dashboard.md\"\n          - \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/.pause\"\n        migration_policy: \"dual-read / single-write for 4 weeks\"\n        on_legacy_read:\n          append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"migration\",\"legacyPath\":\"{legacy_path}\",\"canonicalPath\":\"{canonical_path}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n\n      step_acquire_lock:\n        action: \"Acquire the advisory lock defined by the spec_check_protocol before session classification\"\n        command: \"Open {state_paths.lock_file} with exclusive non-blocking advisory locking semantics; fail closed on contention.\"\n        note: \"macOS/BSD locking here is advisory. Stale-lock override is confirm-only or explicit recovery-only.\"\n        # <!-- F-010-B5-01 -->\n        # Lock-cleanup contract: the lock file MUST be released on every terminal exit path that follows acquisition.\n        # Runtimes honoring step_acquire_lock are required to perform this cleanup before halting or pausing.\n        on_halt:\n          action: \"Release {state_paths.lock_file} before any terminal halt branch returns control\"\n          applies_to: [\"step_classify_session.on_invalid_state\", \"step_classify_session.on_completed_session\", \"step_preinit_spec_branch.conflict-detected\"]\n          command: \"Remove or close-with-release {state_paths.lock_file}; failures here are logged but do not block the halt\"\n        on_cancel:\n          action: \"Release {state_paths.lock_file} on user cancel or pause-sentinel detection before sentinel processing\"\n          command: \"Remove or close-with-release {state_paths.lock_file}; cancel completes regardless of cleanup result\"\n        on_workflow_exit:\n          action: \"Release {state_paths.lock_file} as the final step of any workflow exit path (success or failure)\"\n          command: \"Remove or close-with-release {state_paths.lock_file}; idempotent — safe to invoke when already released\"\n\n      step_classify_session:\n        action: \"Classify the session before writing files\"\n        inspect:\n          - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n        classify:\n          fresh: \"None of the three state artifacts exist\"\n          resume: \"Config, JSONL, and strategy all exist and agree on topic/spec folder\"\n          completed-session: \"Resume artifacts exist and config.status == 'complete'\"\n          invalid-state: \"Any partial, missing, or contradictory combination\"\n        outputs:\n          - session_state: \"fresh | resume | completed-session | invalid-state\"\n        on_resume:\n          # T-YML-DPR-01 / R50-001: Resume is a WRITE-PATH. Produces `iteration-NNN.md` + JSONL appends.\n          # Paired with T-DOC-03 Gate 3 trigger addition (resume, save context, save memory, /memory:save).\n          gate3_classification: write-path\n          gate3_rationale: \"resume produces iteration-NNN.md writes and JSONL state-log appends\"\n          log: \"Auto-resume: state artifacts are complete and consistent. Continue the same lineage (sessionId unchanged, generation unchanged, no archive).\"\n          append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"resumed\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"parentSessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"lineageMode\":\"resume\",\"continuedFromRun\":{iteration_count},\"generation\":{generation},\"archivedPath\":null,\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n          skip_to: phase_loop\n        on_restart:\n          action: \"Archive the current research packet under the root-level research_archive/ tree and start a new lineage segment with a fresh sessionId and generation+1.\"\n          command: \"if [ -d {state_paths.packet_dir} ]; then mkdir -p {state_paths.archive_root} && mv {state_paths.packet_dir} {state_paths.archive_root}/{timestamp_slug}; fi\"\n          set:\n            lineage_mode: \"restart\"\n            parent_session_id: \"{prior_session_id}\"\n            generation: \"{prior_generation + 1}\"\n          append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"restarted\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"parentSessionId\":\"{prior_session_id}\",\"lineageMode\":\"restart\",\"generation\":{generation},\"archivedPath\":\"{state_paths.archive_root}/{timestamp_slug}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n          skip_to: step_create_config\n        note_deferred_branches: \"fork and completed-continue are deferred and no longer runtime-supported in this release. The reducer still reads `lineageMode` from config for dashboards and analysis, but only `new`, `resume`, and `restart` are live. See deep-research/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md §Lifecycle Branch Contract for the one-session contract.\"\n        on_completed_session:\n          log: \"Prior session already completed. Do not route directly to synthesis; archive the completed research/ tree or start a fresh packet instead.\"\n          halt: true\n          message: \"Completed deep-research packet detected. Archive or replace the existing research/ tree before starting a new session.\"\n        on_invalid_state:\n          halt: true\n          message: \"Existing deep-research state is incomplete or contradictory. Repair or archive the invalid research packet before continuing.\"\n        on_fresh:\n          action: \"Proceed with a new session\"\n\n      step_create_config:\n        action: \"Create deep-research-config.json from template\"\n        template: .opencode/skills/deep-research/assets/deep_research_config.json\n        populate:\n          topic: \"{research_topic}\"\n          maxIterations: \"{max_iterations}\"\n          # Semantic: newInfoRatio with negative-knowledge emphasis. See SKILL.md §\"Convergence Threshold Semantics\".\n          convergenceThreshold: \"{convergence_threshold}\"\n          stuckThreshold: 3\n          maxDurationMinutes: 120\n          specFolder: \"{spec_folder}\"\n          resource_map_present: \"{resource_map_present}\"\n          # <!-- F-010-B5-04 -->\n          # Honor the parsed --no-resource-map flag from deep-research.md:73 (default true; false when flag is set).\n          # The markdown command parses $ARGUMENTS and binds {resource_map_emit} before this step runs.\n          resource_map.emit: \"{resource_map_emit}\"\n          createdAt: \"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"\n          status: \"initialized\"","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":300,"totalLines":1079,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_start-research-loop_auto.yaml","time":{"start":1781418094709,"end":1781418094717}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_07f72eb8a7cbf848016a2e486e94188191b0f2738fe7be5124"}},"id":"prt_ec4caf074001r7sl6kfpovoM5f","sessionID":"ses_13b36ae6fffeLx31BHseD4QV23","messageID":"msg_ec4cad5800011YyuV7QOcYGBmT"}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1781418095073,"sessionID":"ses_13b36ae6fffeLx31BHseD4QV23","part":{"id":"prt_ec4caf1e0001j0N0ET4QWggV6k","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"39744e5e81dcaf92a97534cfecaaddbe1208174a","messageID":"msg_ec4cad5800011YyuV7QOcYGBmT","sessionID":"ses_13b36ae6fffeLx31BHseD4QV23","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":57834,"input":13547,"output":238,"reasoning":17,"cache":{"write":0,"read":44032}},"cost":0}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1781418096956,"sessionID":"ses_13b36ae6fffeLx31BHseD4QV23","part":{"id":"prt_ec4caf93a001BJ99ulKvPODPZp","messageID":"msg_ec4caf2d7001lW3RcQ7vz5cenm","sessionID":"ses_13b36ae6fffeLx31BHseD4QV23","snapshot":"39744e5e81dcaf92a97534cfecaaddbe1208174a","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781418098863,"sessionID":"ses_13b36ae6fffeLx31BHseD4QV23","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_hj7k9hU6T4NBvrqfeedrhkh1","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_start-research-loop_auto.yaml","offset":301,"limit":420},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_start-research-loop_auto.yaml</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n301:           executionMode: \"auto\"\n302:           lineage.sessionId: \"{AUTO_SESSION_ID}\"\n303:           lineage.parentSessionId: null\n304:           lineage.lineageMode: \"new\"\n305:           lineage.generation: 1\n306:           lineage.continuedFromRun: null\n307:         output: \"{state_paths.config}\"\n308: \n309:       step_create_state_log:\n310:         action: \"Initialize JSONL state log with config record\"\n311:         # <!-- F-010-B5-04 -->\n312:         # Same parsed --no-resource-map flag honored here so config and state_log agree from line 1.\n313:         content: '{\"type\":\"config\",\"topic\":\"{research_topic}\",\"maxIterations\":{max_iterations},\"convergenceThreshold\":{convergence_threshold},\"resource_map_present\":{resource_map_present},\"resource_map\":{\"emit\":{resource_map_emit}},\"createdAt\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"specFolder\":\"{spec_folder}\"}'\n314:         output: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n315: \n316:       step_create_strategy:\n317:         action: \"Create strategy file from template with initial questions\"\n318:         template: .opencode/skills/deep-research/assets/deep_research_strategy.md\n319:         populate:\n320:           topic: \"{research_topic}\"\n321:           key_questions: \"Derive 3-5 key questions from the research topic\"\n322:           known_context: \"None\"\n323:           known_context_summary: \"None\"\n324:           max_iterations: \"{max_iterations}\"\n325:           convergence_threshold: \"{convergence_threshold}\"\n326:         output: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n327: \n328:       step_create_registry:\n329:         action: \"Initialize reducer-owned findings registry\"\n330:         content: '{\"openQuestions\":[],\"resolvedQuestions\":[],\"keyFindings\":[],\"ruledOutDirections\":[],\"metrics\":{\"iterationsCompleted\":0,\"openQuestions\":0,\"resolvedQuestions\":0,\"keyFindings\":0,\"convergenceScore\":0,\"coverageBySources\":{}}}'\n331:         output: \"{state_paths.registry}\"\n332: \n333:       step_enrich_strategy_context:\n334:         action: \"Ensure Known Context is written only after strategy.md exists\"\n335:         condition: \"prior_context_found\"\n336:         edit: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n337:         note: \"Append or replace the Known Context section with prior_context_summary and retained detail from prior_context\"\n338: \n339:       step_enrich_strategy_resource_map:\n340:         action: \"Inject resource-map status into Known Context after strategy.md exists\"\n341:         edit: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n342:         note: \"When resource_map_present is true, append the resource_map_known_context snapshot. When false, append 'resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate'.\"\n343: \n344:       step_detect_spec_present:\n345:         action: \"Classify late-INIT spec.md state after the durable research packet exists\"\n346:         inspect:\n347:           - \"{spec_folder}/spec.md\"\n348:           - \"{state_paths.lock_file}\"\n349:         classify:\n350:           no-spec: \"spec.md is absent before any pre-init mutation\"\n351:           spec-present: \"spec.md exists and approved host anchors are available for bounded mutation\"\n352:           spec-just-created-by-this-run: \"spec.md already carries this run's DR seed markers and should not be reseeded\"\n353:           conflict-detected: \"missing host anchor, duplicate markers, or generated-block ambiguity makes mutation unsafe\"\n354:         outputs:\n355:           - folder_state: \"no-spec | spec-present | spec-just-created-by-this-run | conflict-detected\"\n356:           - normalized_topic: \"Trim, lowercase, and collapse whitespace in research_topic before dedupe checks\"\n357:         append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"spec_check_result\",\"folder_state\":\"{folder_state}\",\"normalized_topic\":\"{normalized_topic}\",\"specPath\":\"{spec_folder}/spec.md\",\"lockPath\":\"{state_paths.lock_file}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n358: \n359:       step_preinit_spec_branch:\n360:         action: \"Run the bounded pre-init spec branch required by spec_check_protocol\"\n361:         protocol_reference: \".opencode/skills/deep-research/references/protocol/spec_check_protocol.md\"\n362:         branches:\n363:           no-spec:\n364:             create: \"{spec_folder}/spec.md\"\n365:             seed_markers:\n366:               - \"<!-- DR-SEED:REQUIREMENTS -->\"\n367:               - \"<!-- DR-SEED:SCOPE -->\"\n368:             requirements_host: \"Seed Requirements from the research ask without broadening scope\"\n369:             scope_host: \"Seed Scope from the research ask without inventing implementation details\"\n370:             set:\n371:               folder_state: \"spec-just-created-by-this-run\"\n372:               validate_spec_doc: true\n373:             append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"spec_mutation\",\"event\":\"spec_seed_created\",\"folder_state\":\"spec-just-created-by-this-run\",\"anchors_touched\":[\"Requirements\",\"Scope\"],\"diff_summary\":\"Seeded Level 1 spec.md from research topic with DR seed markers.\",\"seed_markers\":[\"DR-SEED:REQUIREMENTS\",\"DR-SEED:SCOPE\"],\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n374:           spec-present:\n375:             edit: \"{spec_folder}/spec.md\"\n376:             set:\n377:               validate_spec_doc: true\n378:             idempotency_check:\n379:               host_anchor: \"Open Questions\"\n380:               normalized_match: \"Normalize the existing anchor text by lowercasing, stripping punctuation, collapsing whitespace, and trimming before comparing with {normalized_topic}.\"\n381:               if_match:\n382:                 skip_append: true\n383:                 append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"spec_mutation\",\"event\":\"spec_preinit_context_deduped\",\"folder_state\":\"spec-present\",\"anchors_touched\":[\"Open Questions\"],\"diff_summary\":\"Skipped duplicate pre-init topic append because normalized topic already exists in Open Questions.\",\"normalized_topic\":\"{normalized_topic}\",\"specPath\":\"{spec_folder}/spec.md\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n384:               if_no_match:\n385:                 append_only:\n386:                   - host_anchor: \"Open Questions\"\n387:                     content: \"Add the normalized research topic only if it is not already present.\"\n388:                   - host_anchor: \"Research Context\"\n389:                     content: \"Add a bounded note that deep-research is active for this topic and that research/research.md remains canonical.\"\n390:                 append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"spec_mutation\",\"event\":\"spec_preinit_context_added\",\"folder_state\":\"spec-present\",\"anchors_touched\":[\"Open Questions\",\"Research Context\"],\"diff_summary\":\"Appended bounded pre-init research context for the normalized topic.\",\"normalized_topic\":\"{normalized_topic}\",\"specPath\":\"{spec_folder}/spec.md\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n391:           spec-just-created-by-this-run:\n392:             verify_markers:\n393:               - \"<!-- DR-SEED:REQUIREMENTS -->\"\n394:               - \"<!-- DR-SEED:SCOPE -->\"\n395:             set:\n396:               validate_spec_doc: false\n397:             note: \"Treat already-seeded spec.md as a no-op guard and continue.\"\n398:           conflict-detected:\n399:             append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"spec_mutation\",\"event\":\"spec_mutation_conflict\",\"folder_state\":\"conflict-detected\",\"reason\":\"Pre-init spec.md mutation is ambiguous or unsafe.\",\"specPath\":\"{spec_folder}/spec.md\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n400:             halt: true\n401: \n402:       step_validate_preinit_spec_doc:\n403:         action: \"Run targeted strict validation after any deep-research pre-init spec.md mutation\"\n404:         condition: \"validate_spec_doc\"\n405:         command: \"SPECKIT_RULES=FRONTMATTER_VALID,LEVEL_DECLARED,TEMPLATE_SOURCE,TEMPLATE_HEADERS,PLACEHOLDER_FILLED,SECTIONS_PRESENT,ANCHORS_VALID,SPEC_DOC_INTEGRITY,TOC_POLICY bash .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/spec/validate.sh {spec_folder} --strict\"\n406:         note: \"This enforces the authored-spec markdown structural contract without applying full-packet required-file or completeness checks to workflow-owned research artifacts. It uses the Node validation orchestrator, whose strict path was measured at about 108ms for a fresh Level 3 packet on the local harness.\"\n407: \n408:       step_init_complete:\n409:         log: \"Initialization complete. Config, state, and strategy files created.\"\n410:         set: { current_iteration: 1, current_segment: 1, stuck_count: 0 }\n411: \n412:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n413:   # PHASE 2: ITERATION LOOP\n414:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n415:   phase_loop:\n416:     purpose: Dispatch agent iterations until convergence\n417:     repeat: true\n418:     max_repeats: \"{max_iterations}\"\n419:     steps:\n420: \n421:       step_read_state:\n422:         action: \"Read current state from JSONL and strategy\"\n423:         read:\n424:           - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n425:           - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n426:           - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n427:         extract:\n428:           - iteration_count: \"Count lines where type === 'iteration'\"\n429:           - current_iteration: \"iteration_count + 1\"\n430:           - current_segment: \"Latest segment_start event segment, else 1\"\n431:           - last_newInfoRatio: \"Extract newInfoRatio from last iteration record\"\n432:           - last_focus: \"Extract focus from latest iteration record, else 'none yet'\"\n433:           - ratio_prev: \"Extract newInfoRatio from second-latest iteration record, else 'N/A'\"\n434:           - ratio_latest: \"Extract newInfoRatio from latest iteration record, else 'N/A'\"\n435:           - next_focus: \"Extract 'Next Focus' section from strategy.md\"\n436:           - remaining_questions: \"Count unchecked items in 'Key Questions'\"\n437:           - remaining_questions_list: \"List unchecked key questions from strategy.md\"\n438:           - answered_count: \"Count answered questions from strategy.md\"\n439:           - total_questions: \"Count total questions tracked in strategy.md\"\n440:           - resource_map_present: \"Extract boolean from deep-research-config.json, default false\"\n441:           - resource_map_prompt_line: \"If resource_map_present is true, return 'Resource map: prior-inventoried files are listed in {spec_folder}/resource-map.md; treat them as the exclusion set when hunting for net-new files; flag only missed-from-map candidates as gaps.' Else return 'Resource map: resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate.'\"\n442:           - least_explored: \"First unanswered question not covered by the most recent iteration focus, else first unanswered question\"\n443:           - last_3_summaries: \"Summarize the latest 3 iteration records as 'run N: focus (ratio)'\"\n444:           - latest_status: \"Extract status from latest iteration record, else 'none yet'\"\n445: \n446:       step_check_pause_sentinel:\n447:         action: \"Check for pause sentinel file\"\n448:         check: \"Does {state_paths.pause_sentinel} exist?\"\n449:         if_exists:\n450:           log_event: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"userPaused\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"stopReason\":\"userPaused\",\"sentinelPath\":\"{state_paths.pause_sentinel}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n451:           message: \"Research paused. Delete research/.deep-research-pause to resume.\"\n452:           halt: true\n453:         if_not_exists:\n454:           proceed: true\n455: \n456:       step_graph_convergence:\n457:         action: \"Evaluate coverage-graph convergence before the inline 3-signal vote and persist the graph decision snapshot\"\n458:         bash: 'node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/convergence.cjs --spec-folder \"{spec_folder}\" --loop-type \"research\" --session-id \"{config.lineage.sessionId}\"'\n459:         note: \"Run before the inline vote. STOP from the inline 3-signal vote is allowed only when the graph decision is STOP_ALLOWED or absent.\"\n460:         outputs:\n461:           - graph_decision: \"Tool decision value (CONTINUE | STOP_ALLOWED | STOP_BLOCKED), else null when unavailable\"\n462:           - graph_decision_json: \"JSON-encoded graph decision string, else null\"\n463:           - graph_signals_json: \"Tool signals object, else {}\"\n464:           - graph_blockers_json: \"Tool blockers array, else []\"\n465:           - graph_trace_json: \"Tool trace payload, else []\"\n466:           - graph_convergence_score: \"signals.blendedScore when present, else the best available graph score, else 0\"\n467:         append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"graph_convergence\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"decision\":{graph_decision_json},\"signals\":{graph_signals_json},\"blockers\":{graph_blockers_json},\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n468: \n469:       step_check_convergence:\n470:         action: \"Evaluate stop conditions and combine the inline 3-signal vote with graph convergence\"\n471:         algorithm: |\n472:           1. if iteration_count >= max_iterations: STOP (maxIterationsReached). This terminal cap bypasses quality-guard overrides; record failed guards/blockers as synthesis evidence instead of continuing.\n473:           2. if remaining_questions == 0: STOP (all_questions_answered)\n474:           3. if stuck_count >= config.stuckThreshold: STUCK_RECOVERY\n475:           4. GRAPH-ASSISTED COMPOSITE CONVERGENCE:\n476:                step_graph_convergence already recorded graph_decision, graph_signals_json, graph_blockers_json, and graph_convergence_score for this run.\n477:                The existing inline 3-signal vote still computes the inline STOP candidate and is not replaced.\n478:                signals = []\n479:                Filter: exclude iterations where status == thought from signal inputs (use only evidence iterations)\n480:                a) Rolling average (w=0.30, needs 3+ iterations):\n481:                   avg = mean(last 3 newInfoRatios)\n482:                   stop if avg < convergence_threshold\n483:                b) MAD noise floor (w=0.35, needs 4+ iterations):\n484:                   noiseFloor = MAD(all ratios) * 1.4826\n485:                   stop if latest ratio <= noiseFloor\n486:                c) Question entropy (w=0.35):\n487:                   coverage = answered / total questions\n488:                   stop if coverage >= 0.85\n489:                Redistribute weights for unavailable signals.\n490:                if weighted_stop_score > 0.60: inline_stop_candidate = true\n491:                Combined stop rule: STOP only if the inline 3-signal vote says STOP AND graph_decision is STOP_ALLOWED or absent.\n492:                if inline_stop_candidate and graph_decision == \"STOP_BLOCKED\":\n493:                  decision = \"BLOCKED\"\n494:                  reason = \"blockedStop\"\n495:                  stop_blocked = true\n496:                  blocked_by_json = JSON array derived from graph_blockers_json\n497:                  blocked_by_csv = comma-separated blocker names derived from graph_blockers_json\n498:                  gate_convergence_pass = false\n499:                  gate_convergence_score = graph_convergence_score\n500:                  gate_key_question_coverage_pass = no blocker named questionCoverage\n501:                  gate_evidence_density_pass = no blocker named sourceDiversity or evidenceDepth\n502:                  gate_evidence_density_sources = graph_signals_json.sourceDiversity or 0\n503:                  gate_hotspot_saturation_pass = true\n504:                  recovery_strategy = first blocker reason/message, else \"Collect deeper graph evidence before stopping.\"\n505:                else if inline_stop_candidate and (graph_decision == \"STOP_ALLOWED\" or graph_decision is absent):\n506:                  decision = \"STOP\"\n507:                  reason = \"composite_converged\"\n508:                  stop_blocked = false\n509:           5. else: CONTINUE\n510:           6. if decision == \"STOP\" and reason != \"maxIterationsReached\":\n511:                guardResult = checkQualityGuards(state, strategy)\n512:                if not guardResult.passed:\n513:                  log: \"Quality guard failed: {guardResult.violations}. Overriding STOP to CONTINUE.\"\n514:                  decision = \"CONTINUE\"\n515:           See convergence.md for full pseudocode and signal definitions.\n516:           Segment-aware convergence is experimental/reference-only; live workflow uses the current session as a single segment.\n517:         outputs:\n518:           - decision: \"STOP | BLOCKED | STUCK_RECOVERY | CONTINUE\"\n519:           - reason: \"Human-readable stop reason\"\n520:           - stop_blocked: \"Boolean marker set when graph convergence vetoes an inline STOP candidate\"\n521:           - blocked_by_json: \"JSON array of graph blocker names when decision == BLOCKED\"\n522:           - blocked_by_csv: \"Comma-separated graph blocker names when decision == BLOCKED\"\n523:           - gate_convergence_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for the graph-assisted convergence gate\"\n524:           - gate_convergence_score: \"Numeric score recorded from graph convergence\"\n525:           - gate_key_question_coverage_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail derived from graph blocker coverage signals\"\n526:           - gate_evidence_density_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail derived from graph blocker evidence-depth signals\"\n527:           - gate_evidence_density_sources: \"Source-diversity count or equivalent evidence-depth proxy\"\n528:           - gate_hotspot_saturation_pass: \"Research placeholder gate; true unless an explicit blocker sets otherwise\"\n529:           - recovery_strategy: \"One-line hint describing the next research action when decision == BLOCKED or STUCK_RECOVERY\"\n530: \n531:       step_emit_blocked_stop:\n532:         action: \"Persist a first-class blocked_stop event when the legal-stop decision tree returns blocked\"\n533:         if_blocked:\n534:           append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"blocked_stop\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"blockedBy\":{blocked_by_json},\"gateResults\":{\"convergence\":{\"pass\":{gate_convergence_pass},\"score\":{gate_convergence_score}},\"keyQuestionCoverage\":{\"pass\":{gate_key_question_coverage_pass},\"answered\":{answered_count},\"total\":{total_questions}},\"evidenceDensity\":{\"pass\":{gate_evidence_density_pass},\"sources\":{gate_evidence_density_sources}},\"hotspotSaturation\":{\"pass\":{gate_hotspot_saturation_pass}}},\"recoveryStrategy\":\"{recovery_strategy}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n535:           log: \"Graph convergence blocked STOP. Failed blockers: {blocked_by_csv}. Recovery strategy: {recovery_strategy}\"\n536:           set:\n537:             decision: \"CONTINUE\"\n538:             reason: \"blockedStop\"\n539:             stop_blocked: false\n540: \n541:       step_handle_convergence:\n542:         action: \"Act on convergence decision\"\n543:         if_stop:\n544:           log: \"Loop stopping. Reason: {reason}\"\n545:           skip_to: phase_synthesis\n546:         if_stuck_recovery:\n547:           append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"stuckRecovery\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"stopReason\":\"stuckRecovery\",\"fromIteration\":{current_iteration},\"outcome\":\"recovered\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n548:           log: \"Stuck detected ({stuck_count} consecutive no-progress). Entering recovery.\"\n549:           set: { next_focus: \"RECOVERY: Widen scope. Try fundamentally different approach. Least-explored question: {least_explored}\" }\n550:           reset: { stuck_count: 0 }\n551:         if_continue:\n552:           log: \"Iteration {current_iteration}: Continuing. Focus: {next_focus}\"\n553: \n554:       step_normalize_pause_events:\n555:         action: \"Normalize pause and recovery lifecycle events to the frozen STOP_REASONS enum at emission time\"\n556:         stop_reasons_enum: [converged, maxIterationsReached, blockedStop, stuckRecovery, error, manualStop, userPaused]\n557:         rule_pause_sentinel:\n558:           raw_event_forbidden: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"paused\"}'\n559:           canonical_event: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"userPaused\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"stopReason\":\"userPaused\",\"sentinelPath\":\"{state_paths.pause_sentinel}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n560:         rule_stuck_recovery:\n561:           raw_event_forbidden: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"stuck_recovery\"}'\n562:           canonical_event: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"stuckRecovery\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"stopReason\":\"stuckRecovery\",\"fromIteration\":{current_iteration},\"outcome\":\"recovered\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n563: \n564:       step_marker_scan:\n565:         action: \"H-2 loop-prevention guard: scan previous iteration's rendered prompt for nested research marker\"\n566:         algorithm: |\n567:           if current_iteration > 1:\n568:             PREV_PROMPT_PATH = \"{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{previous_iteration}.md\"\n569:             if file_exists(PREV_PROMPT_PATH):\n570:               PREV_PROMPT_FIRST_LINE = head -1 of PREV_PROMPT_PATH\n571:               if PREV_PROMPT_FIRST_LINE matches ^(DEEP-REVIEW|DEEP-RESEARCH|CODE-REVIEW)$:\n572:                 log \"ERROR: nested research-of-review loop detected (marker found in previous iteration prompt). Aborting.\"\n573:                 halt with exit code 2\n574:         note: |\n575:           False-positive prevention: only matches when the first line is exactly one of the\n576:           three canonical markers. Markers appearing in comments or body text are ignored.\n577:           True-positive triggers only when a previous iteration's rendered prompt literally\n578:           starts with a deep-loop marker, indicating a nested research-of-review dispatch.\n579: \n580:       step_dispatch_iteration:\n581:         action: \"Dispatch one iteration via the selected executor\"\n582:         resolve_executor:\n583:           source: \"config.executor\"\n584:           loader: \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts#parseExecutorConfig\"\n585:         pre_dispatch:\n586:           generate_summary: |\n587:             STATE SUMMARY (auto-generated):\n588:             Segment: {current_segment} | Iteration: {current_iteration} of {max_iterations}\n589:             Questions: {answered_count}/{total_questions} answered | Last focus: {last_focus}\n590:             Last 2 ratios: {ratio_prev} -> {ratio_latest} | Stuck count: {stuck_count}\n591:             {resource_map_prompt_line}\n592:             Next focus: {next_focus}\n593:           render_prompt_pack:\n594:             template_path: \".opencode/skills/deep-research/assets/prompt_pack_iteration.md.tmpl\"\n595:             renderer: \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/prompt-pack.ts#renderPromptPack\"\n596:             output_path: \"{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md\"\n597:             variables:\n598:               state_summary: \"{state_summary}\"\n599:               research_topic: \"{research_topic}\"\n600:               current_iteration: \"{current_iteration}\"\n601:               max_iterations: \"{max_iterations}\"\n602:               next_focus: \"{next_focus}\"\n603:               remaining_questions_list: \"{remaining_questions_list}\"\n604:               last_3_summaries: \"{last_3_summaries}\"\n605:               state_paths_config: \"{state_paths.config}\"\n606:               state_paths_state_log: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n607:               state_paths_strategy: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n608:               state_paths_registry: \"{state_paths.registry}\"\n609:               state_paths_iteration_pattern: \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\"\n610:               state_paths_delta_pattern: \"{state_paths.delta_pattern}\"\n611:         pre_dispatch_audit:\n612:           skip_when: \"config.executor.type == 'native'\"\n613:           call: \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-audit.ts#writeFirstRecordExecutor\"\n614:           args:\n615:             stateLogPath: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n616:             executor: \"{config.executor}\"\n617:             iteration: \"{current_iteration}\"\n618:         branch_on: \"config.executor.type\"\n619:         if_native:\n620:           dispatch:\n621:             agent: deep-research\n622:             model: opus\n623:             context_source: \"rendered_prompt_pack\"\n624:           wait_for_completion: true\n625:         if_cli_codex:\n626:           command: |\n627:             node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n628:             import { readFileSync } from 'node:fs';\n629: \n630:             import { runAuditedExecutorCommand } from './.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-audit.ts';\n631:             import { resolveCodexSandboxMode } from './.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts';\n632: \n633:             const executor = {\n634:               kind: 'cli-codex',\n635:               model: '{config.executor.model}',\n636:               reasoningEffort: '{config.executor.reasoningEffort}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.reasoningEffort}',\n637:               serviceTier: '{config.executor.serviceTier}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.serviceTier}',\n638:               sandboxMode: '{config.executor.sandboxMode}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.sandboxMode}',\n639:               timeoutSeconds: Number('{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}'),\n640:             };\n641: \n642:             process.exit(\n643:               runAuditedExecutorCommand({\n644:                 command: 'codex',\n645:                 args: [\n646:                   'exec',\n647:                   '--model',\n648:                   executor.model,\n649:                   '-c',\n650:                   `model_reasoning_effort=${executor.reasoningEffort}`,\n651:                   '-c',\n652:                   `service_tier=${executor.serviceTier}`,\n653:                   '-c',\n654:                   'approval_policy=never',\n655:                   '--sandbox',\n656:                   resolveCodexSandboxMode(executor.sandboxMode),\n657:                   '-',\n658:                 ],\n659:                 cwd: '{repo_root}',\n660:                 timeoutSeconds: executor.timeoutSeconds,\n661:                 stateLogPath: '{state_paths.state_log}',\n662:                 executor,\n663:                 iteration: Number('{current_iteration}'),\n664:                 input: readFileSync('{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md', 'utf8'),\n665:               }),\n666:             );\n667:             EOF\n668:           working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n669:           timeout_seconds: \"{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}\"\n670:           wait_for_completion: true\n671:         if_cli_claude_code:\n672:           command: |\n673:             node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n674:             import { readFileSync } from 'node:fs';\n675: \n676:             import { runAuditedExecutorCommand } from './.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-audit.ts';\n677:             import { resolveClaudePermissionMode } from './.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts';\n678: \n679:             const executor = {\n680:               kind: 'cli-claude-code',\n681:               model: '{config.executor.model}',\n682:               reasoningEffort: '{config.executor.reasoningEffort}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.reasoningEffort}',\n683:               serviceTier: '{config.executor.serviceTier}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.serviceTier}',\n684:               sandboxMode: '{config.executor.sandboxMode}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.sandboxMode}',\n685:               timeoutSeconds: Number('{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}'),\n686:             };\n687:             const args = [\n688:               '-p',\n689:               readFileSync('{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md', 'utf8'),\n690:               '--model',\n691:               executor.model,\n692:               '--permission-mode',\n693:               resolveClaudePermissionMode(executor.sandboxMode),\n694:               '--output-format',\n695:               'text',\n696:             ];\n697:             if (executor.reasoningEffort) {\n698:               args.push('--effort', executor.reasoningEffort);\n699:             }\n700: \n701:             process.exit(\n702:               runAuditedExecutorCommand({\n703:                 command: 'claude',\n704:                 args,\n705:                 cwd: '{repo_root}',\n706:                 timeoutSeconds: executor.timeoutSeconds,\n707:                 stateLogPath: '{state_paths.state_log}',\n708:                 executor,\n709:                 iteration: Number('{current_iteration}'),\n710:               }),\n711:             );\n712:             EOF\n713:           working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n714:           timeout_seconds: \"{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}\"\n715:           wait_for_completion: true\n716:           notes:\n717:             - \"sandboxMode maps to permission-mode: read-only -> plan, workspace-write -> acceptEdits, danger-full-access -> bypassPermissions\"\n718:             - \"claude-code has no serviceTier flag\"\n719:             - \"claude-code supports --effort for reasoning depth\"\n720:         record_executor_audit:\n\n(Showing lines 301-720 of 1079. Use offset=721 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"          executionMode: \"auto\"\n          lineage.sessionId: \"{AUTO_SESSION_ID}\"\n          lineage.parentSessionId: null\n          lineage.lineageMode: \"new\"\n          lineage.generation: 1\n          lineage.continuedFromRun: null\n        output: \"{state_paths.config}\"\n\n      step_create_state_log:\n        action: \"Initialize JSONL state log with config record\"\n        # <!-- F-010-B5-04 -->\n        # Same parsed --no-resource-map flag honored here so config and state_log agree from line 1.\n        content: '{\"type\":\"config\",\"topic\":\"{research_topic}\",\"maxIterations\":{max_iterations},\"convergenceThreshold\":{convergence_threshold},\"resource_map_present\":{resource_map_present},\"resource_map\":{\"emit\":{resource_map_emit}},\"createdAt\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"specFolder\":\"{spec_folder}\"}'\n        output: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n\n      step_create_strategy:\n        action: \"Create strategy file from template with initial questions\"\n        template: .opencode/skills/deep-research/assets/deep_research_strategy.md\n        populate:\n          topic: \"{research_topic}\"","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_start-research-loop_auto.yaml","text":"          executionMode: \"auto\"\n          lineage.sessionId: \"{AUTO_SESSION_ID}\"\n          lineage.parentSessionId: null\n          lineage.lineageMode: \"new\"\n          lineage.generation: 1\n          lineage.continuedFromRun: null\n        output: \"{state_paths.config}\"\n\n      step_create_state_log:\n        action: \"Initialize JSONL state log with config record\"\n        # <!-- F-010-B5-04 -->\n        # Same parsed --no-resource-map flag honored here so config and state_log agree from line 1.\n        content: '{\"type\":\"config\",\"topic\":\"{research_topic}\",\"maxIterations\":{max_iterations},\"convergenceThreshold\":{convergence_threshold},\"resource_map_present\":{resource_map_present},\"resource_map\":{\"emit\":{resource_map_emit}},\"createdAt\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"specFolder\":\"{spec_folder}\"}'\n        output: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n\n      step_create_strategy:\n        action: \"Create strategy file from template with initial questions\"\n        template: .opencode/skills/deep-research/assets/deep_research_strategy.md\n        populate:\n          topic: \"{research_topic}\"\n          key_questions: \"Derive 3-5 key questions from the research topic\"\n          known_context: \"None\"\n          known_context_summary: \"None\"\n          max_iterations: \"{max_iterations}\"\n          convergence_threshold: \"{convergence_threshold}\"\n        output: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n\n      step_create_registry:\n        action: \"Initialize reducer-owned findings registry\"\n        content: '{\"openQuestions\":[],\"resolvedQuestions\":[],\"keyFindings\":[],\"ruledOutDirections\":[],\"metrics\":{\"iterationsCompleted\":0,\"openQuestions\":0,\"resolvedQuestions\":0,\"keyFindings\":0,\"convergenceScore\":0,\"coverageBySources\":{}}}'\n        output: \"{state_paths.registry}\"\n\n      step_enrich_strategy_context:\n        action: \"Ensure Known Context is written only after strategy.md exists\"\n        condition: \"prior_context_found\"\n        edit: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n        note: \"Append or replace the Known Context section with prior_context_summary and retained detail from prior_context\"\n\n      step_enrich_strategy_resource_map:\n        action: \"Inject resource-map status into Known Context after strategy.md exists\"\n        edit: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n        note: \"When resource_map_present is true, append the resource_map_known_context snapshot. When false, append 'resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate'.\"\n\n      step_detect_spec_present:\n        action: \"Classify late-INIT spec.md state after the durable research packet exists\"\n        inspect:\n          - \"{spec_folder}/spec.md\"\n          - \"{state_paths.lock_file}\"\n        classify:\n          no-spec: \"spec.md is absent before any pre-init mutation\"\n          spec-present: \"spec.md exists and approved host anchors are available for bounded mutation\"\n          spec-just-created-by-this-run: \"spec.md already carries this run's DR seed markers and should not be reseeded\"\n          conflict-detected: \"missing host anchor, duplicate markers, or generated-block ambiguity makes mutation unsafe\"\n        outputs:\n          - folder_state: \"no-spec | spec-present | spec-just-created-by-this-run | conflict-detected\"\n          - normalized_topic: \"Trim, lowercase, and collapse whitespace in research_topic before dedupe checks\"\n        append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"spec_check_result\",\"folder_state\":\"{folder_state}\",\"normalized_topic\":\"{normalized_topic}\",\"specPath\":\"{spec_folder}/spec.md\",\"lockPath\":\"{state_paths.lock_file}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n\n      step_preinit_spec_branch:\n        action: \"Run the bounded pre-init spec branch required by spec_check_protocol\"\n        protocol_reference: \".opencode/skills/deep-research/references/protocol/spec_check_protocol.md\"\n        branches:\n          no-spec:\n            create: \"{spec_folder}/spec.md\"\n            seed_markers:\n              - \"<!-- DR-SEED:REQUIREMENTS -->\"\n              - \"<!-- DR-SEED:SCOPE -->\"\n            requirements_host: \"Seed Requirements from the research ask without broadening scope\"\n            scope_host: \"Seed Scope from the research ask without inventing implementation details\"\n            set:\n              folder_state: \"spec-just-created-by-this-run\"\n              validate_spec_doc: true\n            append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"spec_mutation\",\"event\":\"spec_seed_created\",\"folder_state\":\"spec-just-created-by-this-run\",\"anchors_touched\":[\"Requirements\",\"Scope\"],\"diff_summary\":\"Seeded Level 1 spec.md from research topic with DR seed markers.\",\"seed_markers\":[\"DR-SEED:REQUIREMENTS\",\"DR-SEED:SCOPE\"],\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n          spec-present:\n            edit: \"{spec_folder}/spec.md\"\n            set:\n              validate_spec_doc: true\n            idempotency_check:\n              host_anchor: \"Open Questions\"\n              normalized_match: \"Normalize the existing anchor text by lowercasing, stripping punctuation, collapsing whitespace, and trimming before comparing with {normalized_topic}.\"\n              if_match:\n                skip_append: true\n                append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"spec_mutation\",\"event\":\"spec_preinit_context_deduped\",\"folder_state\":\"spec-present\",\"anchors_touched\":[\"Open Questions\"],\"diff_summary\":\"Skipped duplicate pre-init topic append because normalized topic already exists in Open Questions.\",\"normalized_topic\":\"{normalized_topic}\",\"specPath\":\"{spec_folder}/spec.md\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n              if_no_match:\n                append_only:\n                  - host_anchor: \"Open Questions\"\n                    content: \"Add the normalized research topic only if it is not already present.\"\n                  - host_anchor: \"Research Context\"\n                    content: \"Add a bounded note that deep-research is active for this topic and that research/research.md remains canonical.\"\n                append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"spec_mutation\",\"event\":\"spec_preinit_context_added\",\"folder_state\":\"spec-present\",\"anchors_touched\":[\"Open Questions\",\"Research Context\"],\"diff_summary\":\"Appended bounded pre-init research context for the normalized topic.\",\"normalized_topic\":\"{normalized_topic}\",\"specPath\":\"{spec_folder}/spec.md\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n          spec-just-created-by-this-run:\n            verify_markers:\n              - \"<!-- DR-SEED:REQUIREMENTS -->\"\n              - \"<!-- DR-SEED:SCOPE -->\"\n            set:\n              validate_spec_doc: false\n            note: \"Treat already-seeded spec.md as a no-op guard and continue.\"\n          conflict-detected:\n            append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"spec_mutation\",\"event\":\"spec_mutation_conflict\",\"folder_state\":\"conflict-detected\",\"reason\":\"Pre-init spec.md mutation is ambiguous or unsafe.\",\"specPath\":\"{spec_folder}/spec.md\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n            halt: true\n\n      step_validate_preinit_spec_doc:\n        action: \"Run targeted strict validation after any deep-research pre-init spec.md mutation\"\n        condition: \"validate_spec_doc\"\n        command: \"SPECKIT_RULES=FRONTMATTER_VALID,LEVEL_DECLARED,TEMPLATE_SOURCE,TEMPLATE_HEADERS,PLACEHOLDER_FILLED,SECTIONS_PRESENT,ANCHORS_VALID,SPEC_DOC_INTEGRITY,TOC_POLICY bash .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/spec/validate.sh {spec_folder} --strict\"\n        note: \"This enforces the authored-spec markdown structural contract without applying full-packet required-file or completeness checks to workflow-owned research artifacts. It uses the Node validation orchestrator, whose strict path was measured at about 108ms for a fresh Level 3 packet on the local harness.\"\n\n      step_init_complete:\n        log: \"Initialization complete. Config, state, and strategy files created.\"\n        set: { current_iteration: 1, current_segment: 1, stuck_count: 0 }\n\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  # PHASE 2: ITERATION LOOP\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  phase_loop:\n    purpose: Dispatch agent iterations until convergence\n    repeat: true\n    max_repeats: \"{max_iterations}\"\n    steps:\n\n      step_read_state:\n        action: \"Read current state from JSONL and strategy\"\n        read:\n          - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n        extract:\n          - iteration_count: \"Count lines where type === 'iteration'\"\n          - current_iteration: \"iteration_count + 1\"\n          - current_segment: \"Latest segment_start event segment, else 1\"\n          - last_newInfoRatio: \"Extract newInfoRatio from last iteration record\"\n          - last_focus: \"Extract focus from latest iteration record, else 'none yet'\"\n          - ratio_prev: \"Extract newInfoRatio from second-latest iteration record, else 'N/A'\"\n          - ratio_latest: \"Extract newInfoRatio from latest iteration record, else 'N/A'\"\n          - next_focus: \"Extract 'Next Focus' section from strategy.md\"\n          - remaining_questions: \"Count unchecked items in 'Key Questions'\"\n          - remaining_questions_list: \"List unchecked key questions from strategy.md\"\n          - answered_count: \"Count answered questions from strategy.md\"\n          - total_questions: \"Count total questions tracked in strategy.md\"\n          - resource_map_present: \"Extract boolean from deep-research-config.json, default false\"\n          - resource_map_prompt_line: \"If resource_map_present is true, return 'Resource map: prior-inventoried files are listed in {spec_folder}/resource-map.md; treat them as the exclusion set when hunting for net-new files; flag only missed-from-map candidates as gaps.' Else return 'Resource map: resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate.'\"\n          - least_explored: \"First unanswered question not covered by the most recent iteration focus, else first unanswered question\"\n          - last_3_summaries: \"Summarize the latest 3 iteration records as 'run N: focus (ratio)'\"\n          - latest_status: \"Extract status from latest iteration record, else 'none yet'\"\n\n      step_check_pause_sentinel:\n        action: \"Check for pause sentinel file\"\n        check: \"Does {state_paths.pause_sentinel} exist?\"\n        if_exists:\n          log_event: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"userPaused\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"stopReason\":\"userPaused\",\"sentinelPath\":\"{state_paths.pause_sentinel}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n          message: \"Research paused. Delete research/.deep-research-pause to resume.\"\n          halt: true\n        if_not_exists:\n          proceed: true\n\n      step_graph_convergence:\n        action: \"Evaluate coverage-graph convergence before the inline 3-signal vote and persist the graph decision snapshot\"\n        bash: 'node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/convergence.cjs --spec-folder \"{spec_folder}\" --loop-type \"research\" --session-id \"{config.lineage.sessionId}\"'\n        note: \"Run before the inline vote. STOP from the inline 3-signal vote is allowed only when the graph decision is STOP_ALLOWED or absent.\"\n        outputs:\n          - graph_decision: \"Tool decision value (CONTINUE | STOP_ALLOWED | STOP_BLOCKED), else null when unavailable\"\n          - graph_decision_json: \"JSON-encoded graph decision string, else null\"\n          - graph_signals_json: \"Tool signals object, else {}\"\n          - graph_blockers_json: \"Tool blockers array, else []\"\n          - graph_trace_json: \"Tool trace payload, else []\"\n          - graph_convergence_score: \"signals.blendedScore when present, else the best available graph score, else 0\"\n        append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"graph_convergence\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"decision\":{graph_decision_json},\"signals\":{graph_signals_json},\"blockers\":{graph_blockers_json},\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n\n      step_check_convergence:\n        action: \"Evaluate stop conditions and combine the inline 3-signal vote with graph convergence\"\n        algorithm: |\n          1. if iteration_count >= max_iterations: STOP (maxIterationsReached). This terminal cap bypasses quality-guard overrides; record failed guards/blockers as synthesis evidence instead of continuing.\n          2. if remaining_questions == 0: STOP (all_questions_answered)\n          3. if stuck_count >= config.stuckThreshold: STUCK_RECOVERY\n          4. GRAPH-ASSISTED COMPOSITE CONVERGENCE:\n               step_graph_convergence already recorded graph_decision, graph_signals_json, graph_blockers_json, and graph_convergence_score for this run.\n               The existing inline 3-signal vote still computes the inline STOP candidate and is not replaced.\n               signals = []\n               Filter: exclude iterations where status == thought from signal inputs (use only evidence iterations)\n               a) Rolling average (w=0.30, needs 3+ iterations):\n                  avg = mean(last 3 newInfoRatios)\n                  stop if avg < convergence_threshold\n               b) MAD noise floor (w=0.35, needs 4+ iterations):\n                  noiseFloor = MAD(all ratios) * 1.4826\n                  stop if latest ratio <= noiseFloor\n               c) Question entropy (w=0.35):\n                  coverage = answered / total questions\n                  stop if coverage >= 0.85\n               Redistribute weights for unavailable signals.\n               if weighted_stop_score > 0.60: inline_stop_candidate = true\n               Combined stop rule: STOP only if the inline 3-signal vote says STOP AND graph_decision is STOP_ALLOWED or absent.\n               if inline_stop_candidate and graph_decision == \"STOP_BLOCKED\":\n                 decision = \"BLOCKED\"\n                 reason = \"blockedStop\"\n                 stop_blocked = true\n                 blocked_by_json = JSON array derived from graph_blockers_json\n                 blocked_by_csv = comma-separated blocker names derived from graph_blockers_json\n                 gate_convergence_pass = false\n                 gate_convergence_score = graph_convergence_score\n                 gate_key_question_coverage_pass = no blocker named questionCoverage\n                 gate_evidence_density_pass = no blocker named sourceDiversity or evidenceDepth\n                 gate_evidence_density_sources = graph_signals_json.sourceDiversity or 0\n                 gate_hotspot_saturation_pass = true\n                 recovery_strategy = first blocker reason/message, else \"Collect deeper graph evidence before stopping.\"\n               else if inline_stop_candidate and (graph_decision == \"STOP_ALLOWED\" or graph_decision is absent):\n                 decision = \"STOP\"\n                 reason = \"composite_converged\"\n                 stop_blocked = false\n          5. else: CONTINUE\n          6. if decision == \"STOP\" and reason != \"maxIterationsReached\":\n               guardResult = checkQualityGuards(state, strategy)\n               if not guardResult.passed:\n                 log: \"Quality guard failed: {guardResult.violations}. Overriding STOP to CONTINUE.\"\n                 decision = \"CONTINUE\"\n          See convergence.md for full pseudocode and signal definitions.\n          Segment-aware convergence is experimental/reference-only; live workflow uses the current session as a single segment.\n        outputs:\n          - decision: \"STOP | BLOCKED | STUCK_RECOVERY | CONTINUE\"\n          - reason: \"Human-readable stop reason\"\n          - stop_blocked: \"Boolean marker set when graph convergence vetoes an inline STOP candidate\"\n          - blocked_by_json: \"JSON array of graph blocker names when decision == BLOCKED\"\n          - blocked_by_csv: \"Comma-separated graph blocker names when decision == BLOCKED\"\n          - gate_convergence_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for the graph-assisted convergence gate\"\n          - gate_convergence_score: \"Numeric score recorded from graph convergence\"\n          - gate_key_question_coverage_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail derived from graph blocker coverage signals\"\n          - gate_evidence_density_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail derived from graph blocker evidence-depth signals\"\n          - gate_evidence_density_sources: \"Source-diversity count or equivalent evidence-depth proxy\"\n          - gate_hotspot_saturation_pass: \"Research placeholder gate; true unless an explicit blocker sets otherwise\"\n          - recovery_strategy: \"One-line hint describing the next research action when decision == BLOCKED or STUCK_RECOVERY\"\n\n      step_emit_blocked_stop:\n        action: \"Persist a first-class blocked_stop event when the legal-stop decision tree returns blocked\"\n        if_blocked:\n          append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"blocked_stop\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"blockedBy\":{blocked_by_json},\"gateResults\":{\"convergence\":{\"pass\":{gate_convergence_pass},\"score\":{gate_convergence_score}},\"keyQuestionCoverage\":{\"pass\":{gate_key_question_coverage_pass},\"answered\":{answered_count},\"total\":{total_questions}},\"evidenceDensity\":{\"pass\":{gate_evidence_density_pass},\"sources\":{gate_evidence_density_sources}},\"hotspotSaturation\":{\"pass\":{gate_hotspot_saturation_pass}}},\"recoveryStrategy\":\"{recovery_strategy}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n          log: \"Graph convergence blocked STOP. Failed blockers: {blocked_by_csv}. Recovery strategy: {recovery_strategy}\"\n          set:\n            decision: \"CONTINUE\"\n            reason: \"blockedStop\"\n            stop_blocked: false\n\n      step_handle_convergence:\n        action: \"Act on convergence decision\"\n        if_stop:\n          log: \"Loop stopping. Reason: {reason}\"\n          skip_to: phase_synthesis\n        if_stuck_recovery:\n          append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"stuckRecovery\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"stopReason\":\"stuckRecovery\",\"fromIteration\":{current_iteration},\"outcome\":\"recovered\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n          log: \"Stuck detected ({stuck_count} consecutive no-progress). Entering recovery.\"\n          set: { next_focus: \"RECOVERY: Widen scope. Try fundamentally different approach. Least-explored question: {least_explored}\" }\n          reset: { stuck_count: 0 }\n        if_continue:\n          log: \"Iteration {current_iteration}: Continuing. Focus: {next_focus}\"\n\n      step_normalize_pause_events:\n        action: \"Normalize pause and recovery lifecycle events to the frozen STOP_REASONS enum at emission time\"\n        stop_reasons_enum: [converged, maxIterationsReached, blockedStop, stuckRecovery, error, manualStop, userPaused]\n        rule_pause_sentinel:\n          raw_event_forbidden: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"paused\"}'\n          canonical_event: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"userPaused\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"stopReason\":\"userPaused\",\"sentinelPath\":\"{state_paths.pause_sentinel}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n        rule_stuck_recovery:\n          raw_event_forbidden: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"stuck_recovery\"}'\n          canonical_event: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"stuckRecovery\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"stopReason\":\"stuckRecovery\",\"fromIteration\":{current_iteration},\"outcome\":\"recovered\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n\n      step_marker_scan:\n        action: \"H-2 loop-prevention guard: scan previous iteration's rendered prompt for nested research marker\"\n        algorithm: |\n          if current_iteration > 1:\n            PREV_PROMPT_PATH = \"{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{previous_iteration}.md\"\n            if file_exists(PREV_PROMPT_PATH):\n              PREV_PROMPT_FIRST_LINE = head -1 of PREV_PROMPT_PATH\n              if PREV_PROMPT_FIRST_LINE matches ^(DEEP-REVIEW|DEEP-RESEARCH|CODE-REVIEW)$:\n                log \"ERROR: nested research-of-review loop detected (marker found in previous iteration prompt). Aborting.\"\n                halt with exit code 2\n        note: |\n          False-positive prevention: only matches when the first line is exactly one of the\n          three canonical markers. Markers appearing in comments or body text are ignored.\n          True-positive triggers only when a previous iteration's rendered prompt literally\n          starts with a deep-loop marker, indicating a nested research-of-review dispatch.\n\n      step_dispatch_iteration:\n        action: \"Dispatch one iteration via the selected executor\"\n        resolve_executor:\n          source: \"config.executor\"\n          loader: \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts#parseExecutorConfig\"\n        pre_dispatch:\n          generate_summary: |\n            STATE SUMMARY (auto-generated):\n            Segment: {current_segment} | Iteration: {current_iteration} of {max_iterations}\n            Questions: {answered_count}/{total_questions} answered | Last focus: {last_focus}\n            Last 2 ratios: {ratio_prev} -> {ratio_latest} | Stuck count: {stuck_count}\n            {resource_map_prompt_line}\n            Next focus: {next_focus}\n          render_prompt_pack:\n            template_path: \".opencode/skills/deep-research/assets/prompt_pack_iteration.md.tmpl\"\n            renderer: \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/prompt-pack.ts#renderPromptPack\"\n            output_path: \"{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md\"\n            variables:\n              state_summary: \"{state_summary}\"\n              research_topic: \"{research_topic}\"\n              current_iteration: \"{current_iteration}\"\n              max_iterations: \"{max_iterations}\"\n              next_focus: \"{next_focus}\"\n              remaining_questions_list: \"{remaining_questions_list}\"\n              last_3_summaries: \"{last_3_summaries}\"\n              state_paths_config: \"{state_paths.config}\"\n              state_paths_state_log: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n              state_paths_strategy: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n              state_paths_registry: \"{state_paths.registry}\"\n              state_paths_iteration_pattern: \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\"\n              state_paths_delta_pattern: \"{state_paths.delta_pattern}\"\n        pre_dispatch_audit:\n          skip_when: \"config.executor.type == 'native'\"\n          call: \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-audit.ts#writeFirstRecordExecutor\"\n          args:\n            stateLogPath: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n            executor: \"{config.executor}\"\n            iteration: \"{current_iteration}\"\n        branch_on: \"config.executor.type\"\n        if_native:\n          dispatch:\n            agent: deep-research\n            model: opus\n            context_source: \"rendered_prompt_pack\"\n          wait_for_completion: true\n        if_cli_codex:\n          command: |\n            node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n            import { readFileSync } from 'node:fs';\n\n            import { runAuditedExecutorCommand } from './.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-audit.ts';\n            import { resolveCodexSandboxMode } from './.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts';\n\n            const executor = {\n              kind: 'cli-codex',\n              model: '{config.executor.model}',\n              reasoningEffort: '{config.executor.reasoningEffort}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.reasoningEffort}',\n              serviceTier: '{config.executor.serviceTier}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.serviceTier}',\n              sandboxMode: '{config.executor.sandboxMode}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.sandboxMode}',\n              timeoutSeconds: Number('{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}'),\n            };\n\n            process.exit(\n              runAuditedExecutorCommand({\n                command: 'codex',\n                args: [\n                  'exec',\n                  '--model',\n                  executor.model,\n                  '-c',\n                  `model_reasoning_effort=${executor.reasoningEffort}`,\n                  '-c',\n                  `service_tier=${executor.serviceTier}`,\n                  '-c',\n                  'approval_policy=never',\n                  '--sandbox',\n                  resolveCodexSandboxMode(executor.sandboxMode),\n                  '-',\n                ],\n                cwd: '{repo_root}',\n                timeoutSeconds: executor.timeoutSeconds,\n                stateLogPath: '{state_paths.state_log}',\n                executor,\n                iteration: Number('{current_iteration}'),\n                input: readFileSync('{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md', 'utf8'),\n              }),\n            );\n            EOF\n          working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n          timeout_seconds: \"{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}\"\n          wait_for_completion: true\n        if_cli_claude_code:\n          command: |\n            node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n            import { readFileSync } from 'node:fs';\n\n            import { runAuditedExecutorCommand } from './.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-audit.ts';\n            import { resolveClaudePermissionMode } from './.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts';\n\n            const executor = {\n              kind: 'cli-claude-code',\n              model: '{config.executor.model}',\n              reasoningEffort: '{config.executor.reasoningEffort}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.reasoningEffort}',\n              serviceTier: '{config.executor.serviceTier}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.serviceTier}',\n              sandboxMode: '{config.executor.sandboxMode}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.sandboxMode}',\n              timeoutSeconds: Number('{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}'),\n            };\n            const args = [\n              '-p',\n              readFileSync('{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md', 'utf8'),\n              '--model',\n              executor.model,\n              '--permission-mode',\n              resolveClaudePermissionMode(executor.sandboxMode),\n              '--output-format',\n              'text',\n            ];\n            if (executor.reasoningEffort) {\n              args.push('--effort', executor.reasoningEffort);\n            }\n\n            process.exit(\n              runAuditedExecutorCommand({\n                command: 'claude',\n                args,\n                cwd: '{repo_root}',\n                timeoutSeconds: executor.timeoutSeconds,\n                stateLogPath: '{state_paths.state_log}',\n                executor,\n                iteration: Number('{current_iteration}'),\n              }),\n            );\n            EOF\n          working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n          timeout_seconds: \"{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}\"\n          wait_for_completion: true\n          notes:\n            - \"sandboxMode maps to permission-mode: read-only -> plan, workspace-write -> acceptEdits, danger-full-access -> bypassPermissions\"\n            - \"claude-code has no serviceTier flag\"\n            - \"claude-code supports --effort for reasoning depth\"\n        record_executor_audit:","lineStart":301,"lineEnd":720,"totalLines":1079,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_start-research-loop_auto.yaml","time":{"start":1781418098852,"end":1781418098860}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0e5c4e69cce29971016a2e4871e9448191b9eded42c1cd81d0"}},"id":"prt_ec4cafd22001Ra1XuKQE5PyAgA","sessionID":"ses_13b36ae6fffeLx31BHseD4QV23","messageID":"msg_ec4caf2d7001lW3RcQ7vz5cenm"}}
